INSERT INTO `helpers_blockcontent` (`id`, `key`, `content`)
VALUES
	(1,'highlights','<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/events/webinars\" target=\"_self\">AASHE 2013 Webinars</a><br /> Events</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/publications/2012-publications.html\" target=\"_self\">The Winter 2012 STARS Quarterly Review</a><br />2012 Publications</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://stars-api-documentation.readthedocs.org/en/latest/index.html\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Launches STARS API</a><br /> Interact with STARS in an automated, programmable way.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"../../../../pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/\" target=\"_self\">Sharing Data with Sierra Magazine or The Princeton Review</a><br /> Learn More<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/membership/special_offer\" target=\"_self\"></a><br /><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/registration.html\" target=\"_self\">Renew your STARS Registration and Receive a 50% Discount</a><br /> Register Today!<br /><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/sponsorship-opportunities.html\" target=\"_self\">Become a STARS Sponsor!</a><br /> Get Involved</p>'),
	(51,'pie_viz_summary','<p>Below is a visualization of average scores across categories, subcategories, and credits for all Rated STARS Reports. Click on a category to drill down and then click in the middle to work back up.</p>\r\n<p>Total available point value for a category, subcategory, or credit is represented by the size of the slice. Average score for a category, subcategory, or credit is indicated by the fill within the slice where the radius indicates the average percentage achieved.</p>'),
	(35,'third-parties','<p><strong>Details of Sharing Data</strong><br />Institutions seeking to share data to be considered for publications by The Princeton Review or Sierra magazine may do so through the STARS Reporting Tool or Campus Sustainability Data Collector.&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">In order to share information an institution must take and save a &lsquo;snapshot&rsquo; of data.</span></p>\r\n<p>Only data documented in STARS credits that are marked as &ldquo;Pursuing&rdquo; will be captured in the snapshot. Please note, once a snapshot of data is taken in the Campus Sustainability Data Collector all data previously saved will no longer be accessible. Continuous access of previously taken snapshots is only a <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/data-collector-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefit</a> for STARS Participants. &nbsp;To receive a copy of the data captured in a previously taken snapshot, please contact either <a href=\"mailto:cool.schools@sierraclub.org\" target=\"_self\">Sierra magazine</a> or <a href=\"mailto:surveysupport@review.com\" target=\"_self\">The Princeton Review</a> directly.</p>\r\n<p>At any time Survey Respondents may register for STARS by choosing the \"Purchase a STARS Participant Subscription\" link on the \"Summary\" tab. Registering for STARS will allow your institution to take advantage of the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/data-collector-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefits</a> associated with being a STARS Participant. STARS Participants may also use this link to renew their participation with STARS.</p>\r\n<p>Please note, The Princeton Review and Sierra magazine have a different target audience and therefore may not include data from all institutions in their various publications. &nbsp;Full lists of the fields that&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.sierraclub.org/sierra/surveyquestions/\" target=\"_self\">Sierra magazine</a>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.princetonreview.com/green-data-partnership/\" target=\"_self\">The Princeton Review</a>&nbsp;require for their publications&nbsp;may be found on each organization\'s website.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Step-by-step</strong></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/tool/manage/migrate/\" target=\"_self\">Complete a Version Migration.</a>&nbsp;<span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">A Version Migration is only necessary for those institutions that are not working in the most current version of the STARS (currently v1.2).</span></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\"><a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/tool/manage/migrate/\" target=\"_self\">Complete a Data Migration.</a> A Data Migration is only necessary for those institutions that wish to migrate data from a previous STARS Report or snapshot into the STARS Reporting Tool or Campus Sustainability Data Collector. Please note, migrating previously saved snapshots is only a <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/data-collector-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefit</a> of STARS Participants.</span></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Choose the organization(s) to share your snapshot with by checking the box next to the name of the organization above.</span></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Click the \"save\" button.</span></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Click on the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/tool/aashe-example-university/manage/share-data/\" target=\"_self\">My Snapshots</a> link above.</span></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Click the \"Take a Snapshot of Your Data Now\"</span><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;button.</span></li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Check the \"Confirm\" box and \"Save\" the snapshot. &nbsp;To confirm a snapshot was successfully taken, make sure the &ldquo;Date of Snapshot&rdquo; and &ldquo;STARS Version&rdquo; fields are populated in the &ldquo;Snapshot&rdquo; section at the bottom of your Snapshot list.</span></li>\r\n</ol>'),
	(5,'elig_form_top','    <p style=\'margin: 5px 40px;\'>\r\n    Eligibility requirements for STARS state:\r\n    </p>\r\n    <blockquote style=\'font-style: italic; margin: 10px 60px; color: #555;\'>Any college or university in the United States or Canada may participate in STARS. An institution is defined by having a separate and distinct administration (e.g. president or chancellor). For institutions that may be a part of a larger system, they must have an administration that is separate and distinct from others in the system of which it is a part.</blockquote>\r\n	<p style=\'margin: 5px 40px;\'>\r\n	If an institution or entity does not meet these requirements but you believe that you have a compelling case for the participation of that institution or entity in STARS, please complete the following form. This information will be evaluated by the STARS staff, who will decide if the institution or entity is eligible to participate in STARS.\r\n	</p>'),
	(2,'reg_unpaid','<p>Thank you for registering for STARS. You can begin using the <a href=\"/tool/\" target=\"_self\">Reporting Tool</a> once we receive payment. For details about the STARS credits, please check out the <a href=\"/pages/about/3993/\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Manual</a>. <br /><br /> If you have questions about STARS, please see our <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/\" target=\"_self\">FAQs</a> or contact the AASHE STARS Team (<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>).</p>'),
	(3,'reg_paid','<p>\r\nThank you for registering for STARS. You can begin using the <a href=\'/tool/\'>Reporting Tool</a> right away. For details about the STARS 1.0 credits, please check out the <a href=\'/pages/about/3993/\'>STARS 1.0 Technical Manual</a>.\r\n<br/><br/>\r\nIf you have questions about STARS, please see our <a href=\'/pages/about/\'>About Section</a> or contact the AASHE STARS Team (<a href=\'mailto:stars@aashe.org\'>stars@aashe.org</a>).\r\n</p>'),
	(4,'refund','<p style=\'font-weight: bold\'>STARS Refund/Cancellation policy</p>\r\n            <p>\r\n            AASHE will honor written requests, submitted to <a href=\'mailto:stars@aashe.org\'>stars@aashe.org</a>, for institutions that would like to withdraw their participation in the STARS program if these institutions have not yet paid the STARS registration fee. AASHE does not offer refunds on registration fees for the STARS program. AASHE holds the right to withdraw any institution from the STARS program that does not comply with the policies and procedures agreed upon when registering for the STARS program.</p>'),
	(6,'register_liaison','<p>The STARS Liaison serves as the main contact for the STARS program\r\n both at their institution and for AASHE.  STARS Liaisons will likely be\r\n contacted by the AASHE staff with updates about the system and should be\r\n easily reached using the contact information provided.  Although any\r\n member of the campus community may fill this role, the STARS program\r\n recommends the individual be very involved in STARS data collection and\r\n documentation on their campus.</p>\r\n<p>The STARS Liaison is the\r\n person responsible for communication with the STARS team. This person will\r\n be able to grant others the ability to submit information using the online\r\n reporting tool.</p>'),
	(7,'dispute_success','<p>\r\n        	Thank you for submitting a STARS Submission Accuracy Inquiry form.\r\n        	Your form has been submitted successfully. \r\n        	Please remember, once the form has been completed and submitted,\r\n        	your comments will be sent directly to the STARS Liaison of the institution in question. \r\n        	In accordance with the <a href=\'http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Submission%20Review%20Proposal.pdf\'>STARS Submission Review Policy</a>,\r\n        	the STARS Team encourages you to work with the STARS Liaison of the institution in question to resolve the issue.\r\n        	If direct communication with the institution in question does not resolve the issue,\r\n        	please contact <a href=\'mailto:stars@aashe.org\'>stars@aashe.org</a> and a STARS staff member will evaluate your STARS\r\n        	submission accuracy inquiry and guide you through the next steps in the process.\r\n        </p>'),
	(8,'accuracy_header','<p>The information in an institution\'s STARS Report is self-reported and is not verified by AASHE or a third party. &nbsp;In accordance with the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/submission_review_policy_june_2012.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Submission Review Policy</a>, you may use this form to report erroneous data you have discovered within an institution&rsquo;s STARS Report.&nbsp;In order for your form to be processed, please complete all required (<span class=\"required_note\">*</span>) fields. Once the form has been completed and submitted, a STARS staff member will evaluate the data accuracy inquiry and will follow-up as appropriate with the institution in question.&nbsp; In submitting a data accuracy inquiry, individuals have the option to remain anonymous to the institution. Please contact <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> if you have any questions about the data accuracy inquiry process.</p>'),
	(54,'migrate_base','<p><strong>Details of Migrating Data</strong><br /> \'Version Migrations\' allow an institution to migrate between different versions of the STARS Technical Manual.&nbsp; For example, an institution may have registered under a version of STARS, such as 1.1, but during the institution\'s subscription to the STARS Reporting Tool another version of STARS was launched, such as 1.2.&nbsp; Completing a \'Version Migration\' will allow the institution to update credits that are outlined in the \'My Submission\' section of the STARS Reporting Tool so that this information reflects the most current version of the STARS credits. Data saved in the STARS Reporting Tool prior to the migration will be visible in the Reporting Tool once the migration is complete.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;Data Migrations&rdquo; allow STARS Participants or Campus Sustainability Data Collector Survey Respondents to migrate previously saved data sets. For example, institutions may choose to pull data from a previously submitted STARS Report, or saved snapshot, into the STARS Reporting Tool or Campus Sustainability Data Collector. Completing a \'Data Migration\' will allow the institution to work off of the specific data set that is migrated instead of documenting data from scratch. Migrating data will replace any previously saved data. This option also allows previous STARS Participants that are now Survey Respondents to move data from a previously published STARS Report from the the Reporting Tool to the Data Collector. &nbsp;Migrating previous snapshots of data is only a benefit for STARS Participants.</p>\r\n<p>Please note that it may take a few minutes for migration to complete, during which time the \'My Submission\' section of the Reporting Tool will be locked. Once the migration is complete your institution&rsquo;s Liaison will receive a confirmation email. <strong>Migrating data will replace any previously saved data and all credits will be marked as &ldquo;In Progress&rdquo; after migration is complete. &nbsp;Scores will reset to zero as a result, but can be reestablished after changing the credit status for each credit.</strong></p>'),
	(9,'credit_dispute','<p>Please explain below why you believe that the data submitted by the institution named above is erroneous.  Please include any information from the institution’s report that is pertinent.</p>'),
	(10,'data_correction_confirm','<p style=\'font-style: italic\'>Please explain in detail below why you believe that the data submitted is incorrect and should be corrected.  Please note the exact text submitted will be posted in your institution’s public STARS Report.</p>'),
	(11,'data_correction_top','<p>The information in an institution\'s STARS Report is self-reported and is not verified by AASHE or a third party. The following form is for STARS Administrators that have realized a mistake has been made when documenting information in the STARS Reporting Tool after the information has been submitted for a STARS Rating and is public on the STARS website.  In order for your form to be processed, please complete all required (*) fields within the form.  Upon submission, the STARS team will review the form to ensure the submitted information reflects a legitimate correction (as opposed to, for example, an update).  Corrections will then be made to the institution’s STARS Report. The corrected information in the institution’s STARS Report will include a date stamp and note that explains the reason for the change and will be publicly available. \r\n</p><p>\r\nIn accordance with the <a href=\'http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Correcting%20Mistakes%20in%20the%20Reporting%20Tool_0.pdf\'>Correcting Mistakes in the Reporting Tool Policy</a>, the STARS Team encourages you to carefully consider the corrections being requested prior to submitting this form.  Please note, the process for making corrections to an institution’s STARS Report will be the same even if the change results in a new rating level.  An institution may make corrections to its STARS Report with no charge up to a year after the STARS submission is received by AASHE.  After that time, any institution-requested corrections require a processing fee of $150 per correction.  Please contact <a href=\'mailto:stars@aashe.org\'>stars@aashe.org</a> with questions or feedback. </p>'),
	(12,'data_correction_success','<p>You have successfully completed this submission.  The STARS team will review your request prior to the information being corrected in the institution’s STARS Report.  The corrected information in the institution’s STARS Report will include a date stamp and note that explains the reason for the change and will be publicly available. </p>\r\n<p>\r\nPlease note, an institution may make corrections to its STARS Report with no charge up to a year after the STARS submission is received by AASHE.  After that time, any institution-requested corrections require a small processing fee of $150 per correction.  Please contact <a href=\'mailto:stars@aashe.org\'>stars@aashe.org</a> with questions or feedback.  \r\n</p>'),
	(13,'register_executive','<p>Since STARS covers the activities of many campus departments and requires the involvement of many individuals, it\'s important that your institution\'s participation has high-level support.  Please provide the contact information for one executive (President, Chancellor, Vice President, Vice Chancellor, or Provost) for AASHE  to copy on the registration confirmation e-mail.  This executive will not be included in subsequent communication and his or her contact information will not be otherwise used.  You may wish to send a message to this person so they know to expect the e-mail from AASHE.   \r\n                </p><p>\r\n            Please note that after all data have been submitted, a letter from the President or Chancellor will be required to earn a STARS Rating.</p>'),
	(14,'extension_request','<p>\r\nPlease confirm that you want to extend your submission deadline by 6 months (exactly 183 days). This change will be applied immediately.\r\n</p>'),
	(19,'data_display_content_second_filter','<p>\r\nUse the drop down menus, below, to find the reporting field of interest (note: begin your search by\r\nselecting a category, then a subcategory, and so on):\r\n</p>'),
	(15,'template_press_release_rated','<p>\r\n<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/template_press_release_for_rated_institutions_with_talking_points.doc\">Template press release announcing STARS Rating</a> (doc)\r\n</p>\r\n		'),
	(16,'template_press_release_unrated','<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/documents/STARS/p_template_press_release_0.doc\" target=\"_self\">Template press release announcing STARS participation</a> (doc)</p>\r\n<p>Charter Participants may modify and use this press release template to announce their participation in STARS.&nbsp;</p>'),
	(17,'migrate_submissionset','<p>You are about to migrate your Submission Set to the latest version of <a href=\"/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS</a>. Please be sure that you are familiar with the record of changes and are aware of how these changes may effect your Submission.</p>\r\n<p>Please allow <strong>1-2&nbsp;</strong><strong>hours</strong> for your data to be migrated. During that time, your active Submission Set will be locked. Once the migration is complete, you will no longer have access to your old Submission Set. You will receive an email confirmation when it is complete.</p>\r\n<p style=\"color: red;\">All credits in your new Submission Set will be reset to \"in progress\". Before you can submit for a STARS Rating or Take a Snapshot, you will need to mark any credits that you wish to pursue as \"pursuing.\"</p>'),
	(18,'data_display_score_second_filter','<p>\r\nSelect up to four categories, subcategories, and/or credits of interest:\r\n</p>'),
	(20,'data_display_content','<p>This STARS Data Display provides exact responses to specific reporting fields in institutions\' STARS Reports. The institutional filter tool will enable you to focus on an increasingly specific group of institutions. For example, if the organization type \"Four Year Institution\" and STARS Rating \"Gold\" is selected only results for four-year institutions that achieved a Gold rating will be displayed. A specific filter can only be used once to narrow your results. To remove a filter, click the grey circle to the left of its name.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Features:</strong> Once you add a filter and apply your content data selections, an Export Results icon will enable content data downloading.&nbsp;Also, be sure to bookmark URLs for later reference and sharing!&nbsp;</p>'),
	(21,'data_display_scores','<p>This STARS Data Display provides scores for particular categories, subcategories, and credits of interest. The filter tool will enable you to focus on an increasingly specific group of institutions. For example, if the organization type \"Four Year Institution\" and STARS Rating \"Gold\" is selected only results for four year institutions that achieved a Gold rating will be displayed. A specific filter can only be used once to narrow your results. To remove a filter, click the grey circle to the left of its name.</p>\r\n<p><strong>New Features:</strong>&nbsp;Once you add a filter and apply your score data selections, an Export Results icon will appear to enable score data downloading. Also, be sure to bookmark URLs for later reference and sharing!&nbsp;</p>'),
	(22,'data_display_categories','<p>\r\nThis STARS Data Display provides average category scores for the groups of institutions that share\r\na particular characteristic. Select filters multiple times to compare different groups of institutions. To remove a group of institutions from the results, click on the grey circle to the left of its name.\r\n</p>'),
	(50,'dash_parts_and_subs','<p><em>STARS Registrations, Submissions, and Renewals over time.</em></p>'),
	(24,'dash_inst_properties','<p><em>Note: The figures listed above all apply to institutions that are either Rated or current STARS Participants, with the exception of Charter and Pilot Participants, who may or may not be&nbsp;Rated or&nbsp;current Participants.</em></p>'),
	(25,'edit_submission_boundary','Please describe the boundaries of the institution\'s STARS submission. If any institution-owned, leased, or operated buildings or other holdings are omitted, briefly explain why.'),
	(26,'terms_of_service','<p><strong>Sustainability Tracking, Assessment and Rating System (&ldquo;STARS&rdquo;)</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>VERSION 1.2</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\">Terms and Conditions of Use</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>1.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Definitions</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The term &ldquo;AASHE&rdquo; refers to the Association for the Advancement of Sustainability in Higher Education (&ldquo;AASHE&rdquo;), a registered non-profit corporation of the State of Massachusetts with authority to transact business in the State of Kentucky, with an address of 213 1/2 N. Limestone, Lexington, Kentucky 40507, and all of its respective employees, agents, officers, directors, assigns and successors in interest.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The term &ldquo;Business Day&rdquo; refers to any day of the week excepting Saturday and Sunday and any U.S. federal holiday.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The words &ldquo;eligible&rdquo; and &ldquo;eligibility&rdquo; refer to whether a Participant meets the STARS criteria, as detailed in STARS 1.2.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The word &ldquo;Participant&rdquo; refers to any eligible institution of higher education that has initiated the STARS Rating Process.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The term &ldquo;STARS 1.2&rdquo; (also referred to as &ldquo;STARS&rdquo;) refers to Version 1.2 of the voluntary, self-reporting framework designed by AASHE to gauge and recognize the relative progress of colleges and universities toward sustainability. &nbsp;Information about STARS and guidelines for participation are located at the website address <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"../../../../users/meghan/Downloads/stars.aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars.aashe.org</a></span>.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.6&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The term &ldquo;STARS Reporting Tool&rdquo; refers to the STARS web interface that allows Participants to upload information relevant to their STARS application or rating.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>1.7&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The term &ldquo;STARS Rating Process&rdquo; refers to the applicable process for submitting and obtaining or maintaining a new or updated STARS rating.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>2.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scope of Binding Agreement</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These Terms and Conditions (&ldquo;Terms&rdquo;) constitute a fully integrated agreement (&ldquo;Agreement&rdquo;) between the Participant and AASHE that supersedes any and all prior agreements between the Participant and AASHE concerning the use of STARS 1.2. If there is a discrepancy or conflict between these terms and any other source of information on STARS Version 1.2, these terms shall govern.&nbsp; These Terms and Conditions shall also apply to use of any future version of STARS, unless otherwise indicated.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>2.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant acknowledges and agrees that, once accepted by clicking on the Terms and Conditions &ldquo;accept&rdquo; button displayed during the online registration process, these Terms are enforceable as a binding contract. &nbsp;By accepting this Agreement, the Participant agrees to be bound by all the terms of this Agreement.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>3. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Eligibility </strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>In accepting these Terms, the Participant accepts that AASHE has the right to grant, withhold, or deny a STARS rating, or to withdraw or revoke a rating previously given, if AASHE determines that the Participant does not meet the eligibility requirements stated in STARS 1.2.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>4. &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Duties of the Participant</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant must submit all data related to obtaining, maintaining, or updating a STARS rating through the STARS Reporting Tool.&nbsp; Only information that is submitted through the STARS Reporting Tool will be considered in awarding the STARS Rating.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In addition to submitting information through the STARS Reporting Tool, the Participant must publish all data, information, and supporting materials related to obtaining, maintaining, or updating its STARS rating on a website that is freely available to the public.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; All information that is submitted for purposes of obtaining, maintaining, or updating a STARS rating must be correct and accurate.&nbsp; Any incorrect or inaccurate information within a submission must be immediately corrected through the STARS Reporting Tool, and in no event shall such corrective action occur later than fifteen (15) Business Days of the Participant&rsquo;s notification or discovery of the inaccuracy.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant must routinely supplement previously-submitted information that has become inaccurate or incorrect due to a change in the underlying factual situation or circumstances of the Participant&rsquo;s submission.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>4.5&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant must timely pay all fees associated with the STARS Rating Process.&nbsp; Failure to pay any fees required by STARS 1.2 in a timely manner, as determined by AASHE, may result in withholding or withdrawal of a STARS rating.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>5.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Rights of AASHE</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In accepting these Terms, the Participant acknowledges that AASHE is the final arbiter in matters relating to the interpretation and application of the STARS Guidelines, including all rating criteria.&nbsp; The Participant further acknowledges that AASHE&rsquo;s determination and interpretation of all aspects of the STARS Guidelines, including applicability, is controlling in any dispute over the meaning or application of the STARS Guidelines.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In accepting these Terms, the Participant acknowledges that AASHE has the right to correct any inaccurate information submitted by a Participant.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In submitting data and information to AASHE for purposes of obtaining, maintaining, or updating a STARS rating, the Participant grants AASHE the right to use the submitted data for purposes of research, reports, publicity, comparison, or other such uses.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>5.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; In accepting these Terms, the Participant acknowledges that AASHE has the right to remove the Participant from the STARS program if the Participant fails to comply with either these Terms and Conditions or the policies and procedures agreed to during the STARS program registration process. <br /> <br /></p>\r\n<p><strong>6.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use and Protection of Intellectual Property</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The intellectual property rights in STARS 1.2 and the materials, programs and processes made available through its use are the sole property of AASHE, a registered 501(c)(3) Public Charity of the State of Massachusetts. &nbsp;STARS 1.2 may contain other proprietary notices and copyright information, the terms of which must be observed and followed. &nbsp;Unless otherwise noted, all information, text, articles, data, images, documents, software or other materials (collectively hereinafter referred to as the \"Materials\") contained in STARS 1.2, including online Materials, are copyrighted by AASHE.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>6.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant may not copy, distribute, sell, or modify the Materials without the express, prior written consent of the Copyright Holder.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>7.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Release and Limitation of Liability</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; None of the parties involved in the funding, creation, or administration of STARS 1.2, including AASHE or its affiliates, employees, volunteers or contractors, assume any liability or responsibility to the Participant, user or any third parties for the accuracy, completeness, or use of or reliance on any information contained in STARS &nbsp;or submitted by Participants, or for any injuries, losses, or damages (including, without limitation, equitable relief) arising from such use or reliance.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; All STARS materials are provided without warranties of any kind, either express or implied, including but not limited to warranties as to the accuracy or completeness of information or the suitability of the information for any particular purpose.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7.3 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant hereby waives and releases all claims, losses, and causes of action against AASHE arising out of, or in any way related to, the use of the STARS system other than claims and causes of action for the Participant&rsquo;s losses, damages, costs or expenses that are the direct and proximate result of AASHE&rsquo;s willful misconduct, gross negligence, or wanton or reckless behavior.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>7.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; AASHE is not responsible for the accuracy or availability of Participant&rsquo;s or any third-party information; AASHE&rsquo;s reference to any information controlled or maintained by any party other than AASHE does not constitute an endorsement or warranty of any kind either express or implied including the implied warranty of merchantability and/or implied warranty of fitness for any particular use.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>8.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Indemnification</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>With respect to any and all uses of STARS 1.2, the Participant agrees to indemnify AASHE for, and to hold AASHE harmless against, any and all third-party claims, judgments, liabilities, causes of action, losses, damages, costs, expenses or any other potential remedy arising from, or in any way related to, the use of STARS 1.2 to the extent that such claim, judgment, liability, cause of action, loss, damage, cost or expense was not caused by AASHE&rsquo;s gross negligence, willful misconduct, or wanton and reckless behavior.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>9.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Mediation</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>With regard to any claim or dispute arising out of the participant&rsquo;s application for a STARS Rating, AASHE will have thirty (30) calendar days after receiving notice of the dispute to elect to refer the claim to non-binding mediation (hereafter referred to as &ldquo;Mediation&rdquo;). &nbsp;If AASHE refers the Participant&rsquo;s claim to Mediation, then the Participant shall not be entitled to commence litigation against AASHE until after the Mediation is completed as documented by a letter from the mediator stating that the Mediation is completed; provided, however, that if there comes a time when the applicable statute of limitations for the Participant&rsquo;s claim will expire within ninety (90) calendar days and the Mediation has not been completed, then the Participant may commence litigation for the sole purpose of satisfying the applicable statute of limitations and the Participant shall immediately stay such litigation until the Mediation is completed. &nbsp;Mediation shall take place in person in the State of Kentucky, United States, before a mediator jointly selected by the Participant and AASHE, and both the Participant and AASHE shall have at least one person attend the Mediation in person who has full authority to settle the Participant&rsquo;s claim. The costs and fees billed by the mediator shall be split and paid equally by the Participant and AASHE.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>10.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Notice of Claims</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>10.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If any Participant or third-party has been damaged by any act or omission of AASHE, then, within thirty (30) calendar days after the occurrence of each such act or omission, the Participant or third-party must provide AASHE with written notice describing with reasonable detail the act and/or omission, how the Participant or third-party was damaged by it, and a reasonable estimate of the extent of monetary amount of the damages the Participant or third-party claims to have suffered. The Participant or third-party must provide this written notice to AASHE by certified mail, return receipt requested, addressed as follows:</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AASHE <br /> 213 &frac12; N. Limestone<br /> Lexington, KY 40507 <br /> <br /></p>\r\n<p>10.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The act of providing AASHE with the notice in the manner and within the time frame described in paragraph 10.1, above, is an EXPRESS CONDITION PRECEDENT to the Participant or third-party&rsquo;s right to commence and maintain litigation against AASHE. The Participant or third-party knowingly and intelligently waives any and all claims and causes of action against AASHE to the extent that the Participant or third-party does not provide AASHE with the notice in the manner and within the time frame described in paragraph 10.1, above. Further, Participant or third-party agrees not to commence litigation against AASHE until sixty (60) calendar days after AASHE receives (as evidenced by AASHE&rsquo;s signature on the return receipt) the written notice described in paragraph 10.1, above. The Participant&rsquo;s and third-party&rsquo;s right to commence and maintain litigation against AASHE is further limited as described in paragraphs 7, 9, and 11 and 12 below.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>11.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Governing Law</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These Terms, and all of the rights and duties of the Participant and AASHE arising out of or related to the use of STARS 1.2, or arising out of or related to the relationship between the Participant and AASHE, are governed by the laws of the State of Kentucky, United States of America, without regard to its conflicts of law rules. &nbsp;This provision applies to all claims and causes of action against AASHE, whether based in law or equity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>12.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Venue</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Participant agrees that any and all claims and causes of action against AASHE shall be commenced in and decided exclusively by a court of competent jurisdiction located in the State of Kentucky, United States of America. The Participant agrees to submit to the personal and exclusive jurisdiction of the courts located in the State of Kentucky, United States of America. The Participant waives all defenses and arguments contending that the courts located in the State of Kentucky, United States of America, constitute an inconvenient forum based upon the Participant&rsquo;s residence, domicile, the location of the project that is the subject of the litigation, the location of witnesses, the location of documents, or any other basis. The Participant knowingly and intelligently waives its right to a jury trial with respect to any and all claims and causes of action against AASHE.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>13.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; No Third-Party Beneficiaries</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>These Terms, and the Agreement, are for the sole and exclusive benefit of the Participant and AASHE. Nothing in these Terms, or the Agreement, shall be deemed to create any third party beneficiaries or confer any benefit or rights on or to any person other than the Participant and AASHE. &nbsp;Only the Participant and AASHE shall be entitled to enforce these Terms and to exercise the rights contained within them.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>14.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Use of the STARS Reporting Tool</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>14.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The STARS Reporting Tool, available online, is designed and administered solely for the purpose of facilitating the STARS rating process. You acknowledge that access to certain sections and use of certain services provided through the STARS Reporting Tool may require the acceptance of additional terms and conditions. Such additional terms and conditions will be presented to you where applicable.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>14.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You agree that your use of the STARS Reporting Tool will be to effect lawful purposes only. Further, you agree that you will not post to or transmit through the STARS Online Reporting Tool any information containing threatening, offensive, abusive, harassing, or defamatory content.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>14.3 &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; You agree that you shall not use the STARS Reporting Tool for the purposes of advertising, to collect site content for commercial purposes including screen scraping, to collect user or project information for commercial purposes, and/or to solicit others with respect to the purchase or sale of products or services.<strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>15.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Withdrawal and Refund Policy</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>15.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant agrees that, prior to payment of the STARS registration fee, the Participant may withdraw from the STARS program by submitting a written request for withdrawal to AASHE at <span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>15.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The Participant acknowledges and agrees that AASHE will not refund any STARS registration fee that has been submitted to and received by AASHE.</p>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>16.&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Miscellaneous</strong></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>15.1&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; If any provision set forth in these Terms and in the Agreement, or the application thereof to any circumstance, shall, to any extent, be found by a court of competent jurisdiction to be invalid, illegal or unenforceable, in any respect the validity, legality and enforceability of the remaining provisions contained herein will not in any way be affected or impaired thereby; AASHE and the Participant will endeavor to replace any invalid, illegal or unenforceable provision as may be necessary or desirable in the circumstances to achieve, as closely as possible, the original intent of the provisions and terms of this Agreement.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>15.2&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; The headings used in this document are for ease of reference only and shall not in any way be construed to limit or alter the meaning of any provision.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>15.3&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Any rule that ambiguities are construed or interpreted against the drafter of a document, or against the party for whose benefit the document is made, shall not apply to these Terms.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>15.4&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; These Terms may only be modified in writing and all such written modifications must be signed by the Participant and the then-current Executive Director or Chair of the Board of Directors of AASHE. &nbsp;No other individuals have the authority to modify these Terms on behalf of AASHE. &nbsp;No action or inaction by AASHE shall be construed as a waiver of this or any other provision of these Terms.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: \'Times New Roman\'; font-size: small;\"><span style=\"line-height: 24px;\"><strong><br /></strong></span></span></p>'),
	(27,'ta_app','<p><em>*Please note the deadline to submit an application has passed.&nbsp;  AASHE is not accepting STARS Technical Advisor Applications at this  time.</em></p>\r\n<p>AASHE seeks individuals with expertise related to campus sustainability to serve as STARS Technical Advisors. 1-2 Technical Advisors are sought for each of the following areas: Grounds, Transportation, Waste, Coordination &amp; Planning, Diversity &amp; Affordability, Sustainable Investment, and Public Engagement. STARS Technical Advisors are the primary source for input and insight regarding the content of STARS credits. Technical Advisors will be drawn from higher education institutions, non-profit organizations, and businesses, with a preference given for AASHE members. You can learn more about the responsibilities of this position by visiting the&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/about/governance/technical-advisors.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Advisors</a> page of the STARS website. In order to be considered please complete the following application. The application deadline is Friday, December 16th, 2011. If you have any questions, please contact&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_blank\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>'),
	(28,'sc_app','<p>AASHE is currently seeking a few campus representatives to join the STARS Steering Committee. In order to be considered for the committee, you must complete the following application and submit a resume. You can learn more about the responsibilities of this position by visiting the&nbsp;<a href=\"/pages/about/governance/steering-committee.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Steering Committee</a> page of the STARS website. To be considered for a position on the STARS Steering Committee, a completed application form must be submitted by Friday, December 7th, 2012. If you have any questions, please contact&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.&nbsp;</p>'),
	(29,'reg_participant_description','<p>STARS is an innovative, voluntary self-reporting framework for colleges  and universities to gauge progress toward sustainability and be  recognized for sustainability leadership. Institutions that register for STARS are recognized as STARS Participants, gain 12-months of continual access to the STARS Reporting Tool, have the ability to save, edit, and share documented data, as well as gain public recognition for completing a STARS Report and earning a STARS Rating. View a complete list of <a href=\"http://stars.stage.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-participant-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefits</a> associated with being a STARS Participant. The STARS registration fee is $900 for AASHE Members and $1,400 for Non-members.&nbsp;</p>'),
	(30,'reg_select_institution','<p>Please select your institution from the list below. If your institution is not listed here please contact us at <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>'),
	(31,'reg_respondent_description','<p>AASHE  has created the <a href=\"../../../../pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/campus-sustainability-data-collector.html\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Data Collector</a> for institutions  not yet participating in STARS. This basic tool  allows any higher  education institution the option to share campus  sustainability data  with The Princeton Review, Sierra magazine, and the  Sustainable  Endowments Institute. The Data Collector is modeled after  the STARS  Reporting Tool and is available at no cost. &nbsp;However, this  option does  not include many of the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-participant-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefits</a> of the STARS Reporting Tool or those  associated with being a STARS Participant.</p>'),
	(32,'register_respondent_liaison_desc','<p>Please provide contact information for the primary contact at your institution. This person may receive period notifications regarding your participation in the Campus Sustainability Data Collector.</p>'),
	(33,'reg_participant_congrats','<p>Congratulations! You have successfully registered as a <strong>STARS Participant.</strong></p>\r\n<p>You can begin working in the <a href=\"/tool/\" target=\"_self\">Data Collector</a> right away.<br /><br /> If you have questions about the Campus Sustainability Data Collector, please see our <a href=\"http://stars.stage.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/faqs.html\" target=\"_self\">FAQs</a>.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 10px 50px;\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>'),
	(44,'reg_respondent_congrats','<p>Congratulations! You have successfully registered as a&nbsp;<strong>Survey Respondent.</strong></p>\r\n<p>You can begin working in the&nbsp;<a href=\"/tool/\" target=\"_self\">Data Collector</a>&nbsp;right away.<br /><br />If you have questions about the Campus Sustainability Data Collector, please see our&nbsp;<a href=\"http://stars.stage.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/faqs.html\" target=\"_self\">FAQs</a>.</p>'),
	(34,'tool_summary_footer','<p><strong>Institutional Boundary</strong><br /> To get started, <a href=\"/tool/submissions/boundary/\" target=\"_self\">edit the institutional boundary</a>. Each institution is expected to include its entire main campus when   collecting data. Institutions may choose to include any other land   holdings, facilities, farms, and satellite campuses, as long as the   selected boundary is the same for every credit. If an institution finds it necessary to  exclude a  particular unit from its submission, the reason for  excluding it must  be provided in the notes accompanying the submitted  data.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Data Documentation and Sharing</strong><br /> To begin documenting your institution\'s data, simply click on the \"My Submission\" link above or in the toolbar on the left side of this webpage. To share data, with The Princeton Review, Sierra magazine, and/or the Sustainable Endowments Institute, choose the \"Share Data\" tab at the top of this page.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Register for STARS</strong><br /> AASHE has created the&nbsp;<a href=\"../../../../pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/campus-sustainability-data-collector.html\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Data Collector</a>&nbsp;for institutions not currently participating in STARS. At any time Survey Respondents may upgrade their participation level and register for STARS by choosing the \"Purchase STARS Participant Subscription\" link above. Registering for STARS will allow your institution to take advantage of the <a href=\"/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/data-collector-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefits</a> associated with being a STARS Participant.</p>'),
	(36,'save_snapshot','<p>The data that will be shared is called a \"snapshot.\" A snapshot will capture all credits that are currently marked as &ldquo;Pursing&rdquo; under <em>My Submission</em>.&nbsp; Please note, Survey Respondents will not have access to the data once a snapshot has been taken. This is only a benefit for STARS Participants.</p>'),
	(37,'manage_accounts','<p>Grant access below by typing the email address and role of the new user. \"Administrator\" users have full access, \"Data Entry\" users may only enter and remove information, and \"Observers\" may only see information in the tool. Choose the \"Add\" button to complete the submission.</p>'),
	(38,'boundary_page','<div>\r\n<p>Each institution is expected to include its entire main campus when collecting data. Institutions may choose to include any other land holdings, facilities, farms, and satellite campuses, as long as the selected boundary is the same for each credit. If an institution finds it necessary to exclude a particular unit from its submission, the reason for excluding it must be provided in the notes accompanying the submitted data.</p>\r\n<p>All information documented in any of the sections below will be displayed with the institution\'s public STARS Report. Please note, the Institutional Boundary applies to current data, not previous submissions or reports.</p>\r\n</div>'),
	(39,'responsible_parties','<p><span>Completing the submission for each credit requires an affirmation from one Responsible Party that the information submitted is accurate. The Responsible Party should be a staff member, faculty member, or administrator who can respond to questions regarding the data. </span>When  a STARS Participants submits a STARS Report for a rating, the  Responsible Party&rsquo;s name will be made public alongside the information  submitted for the credit.</p>\r\n<p>AASHE recommends that Responsible Parties are notified prior to being  listed.&nbsp; A modifiable email template is provided in the \"Template Emails\" section of \"<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/tool/my-resources/\" target=\"_self\">My Resources</a>\" for this purpose.</p>\r\n<p><span>You can add responsible parties here, or within the context of a credit. To edit, please click on the name of the Responsible Party listed. Please note, email addresses listed for Responsible Parties should be associated with an institution.<br /></span></p>'),
	(40,'manage_contact_info','<p>The Liaison serves as the primary contact for your institution.</p>'),
	(41,'manage_payments','<p>Below is a list of payments and the subscription period were for.</p>'),
	(42,'dash_ratings','<p><em>Totals for all versions of STARS.</em></p>'),
	(43,'dash_avg_cat_scores','<p><em>Average scores for all STARS Rated institutions.</em></p>\r\n<p>See more <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/institutions/data-displays/pie-chart-visualization/\" target=\"_self\">Average Scores Visually</a>.</p>'),
	(45,'submit_for_rating_address','<p>Please provide the address of your institution\'s highest ranking executive.&nbsp; This individual will be mailed a letter and certificate acknowledging your institution\'s STARS rating.</p>'),
	(46,'submit_for_rating_letter','<p>Please upload a letter from your institution&rsquo;s highest executive (president or chancellor) in PDF format. Each submittal for a STARS rating must be accompanied by a letter  from  the institution\'s president, chancellor, or highest ranking executive  that affirms the accuracy  of the institution\'s STARS Submission. In  addition, the president or  chancellor\'s letter serves as an  introduction or cover letter for the  submission. As such, the letter  may also include a description of the  institution\'s commitment to  sustainability, background about the  institution, key achievements or  highlights from the STARS submission,  and goals for future submissions.  Sign-off from the institution\'s  president or chancellor is an  important strategy for promoting accuracy  within the STARS  self-assessment framework.</p>'),
	(47,'boundary_characteristics','<p>In this context, institutional characteristics are variables that can take on a range of values. Although AASHE encourages institutions to share as much data as possible, if information requested for a required field is unavailable the field may be left blank and will be noted as \"Not  Available.\"</p>'),
	(48,'boundary_features','<p>In this context, institutional features are entities that either are present or are not present at the institution. Institutions will indicate if feature is present at institution and, of those present, if it is included in institutional boundary.</p>'),
	(55,'data_use_guidelines_message','<p style=\"margin: 0px 130px;\"><em><small> AASHE believes transparency is a key component in communicating sustainability claims. STARS data are made publicly available, and can be used in research and publications, provided that certain  <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/data_use_guidelines.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Data Use Guidelines</a> are met. </small></em></p>'),
	(49,'third-party_snapshots','<p>STARS Participants and Survey Respondents are welcome to take a \"snapshot\" of the data documented in the STARS Reporting Tool or Campus Sustainability Data Collector at any time.&nbsp; Please note, once a snapshot of data is taken by a Data Collector <strong>Survey Respondent</strong> all data previously saved will <strong>no longer be accessible</strong>. Continuous access to stored data is only a <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/data-collector-benefits.html\" target=\"_self\">benefit</a> for STARS Participants. &nbsp;To receive a copy of the data captured in a previously taken snapshot, please contact either <a href=\"mailto:cool.schools@sierraclub.org\" target=\"_self\">Sierra magazine</a> or <a href=\"mailto:surveysupport@review.com\" target=\"_self\">The Princeton Review</a> directly.</p>'),
	(52,'data_migration_warning','<p>By migrating your data from a previous submission, you will be overwriting any data you may have in My Submission. It may take a few minutes to complete the migration, during which time you will be <strong>locked out</strong>&nbsp;of <em>My Submission.</em></p>\r\n<p>Once the migration is complete you will regain access to <em>My Submission</em>&nbsp;and all your data will be available. However,&nbsp;<strong>all credits will be marked as \"In Progress\"</strong> to ensure that you go back in and confirm the data is still accurate before submitting again.</p>\r\n<p>The Innovation credits from your previous report&nbsp;will&nbsp;not migrate to&nbsp;your current Submission&nbsp;because an institution can only claim a particular activity as an innovation credit once. When resubmitting for a STARS rating, an innovation credit that the institution submitted previously cannot be re-submitted. &nbsp;Innovation credits previously submitted are accessible for three years from the date of submission.</p>'),
	(53,'version_migration_warning','<p>It may take a few minutes to complete this migration, during which time you will be&nbsp;<strong>locked out</strong>&nbsp;of&nbsp;<em>My Submission.</em></p>\r\n<p><em></em>This migration will convert your existing submission to the latest version of STARS. If there is no data in your current submission then there <strong>still won\'t be any data</strong> after this migration. If your current submission is empty, but you have a previously rated report, &nbsp;you can import data from there with a&nbsp;<a href=\"/tool/manage/migrate/\" target=\"_self\">Data Migration</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Once this version migration is complete you will regain access to&nbsp;<em>My Submission</em>&nbsp;and all your data will be available. However,&nbsp;<strong>all credits will be marked as \"In Progress\"</strong>&nbsp;to ensure that you go back in and confirm the data is still accurate before submitting again.</p>'),
	(56,'data_migration_alert','<p><strong>Please Note: </strong>Your score will reset and all your credits will be marked as \"In Progress.\"</p>'),
	(57,'dd_app','<p>AASHE provides a number of options for accessing STARS data for sustainability analysis, research, and benchmarking. Current AASHE members enjoy elevated access to certain STARS displays, while current membership in STARS grants the highest level of access to STARS data.</p>\r\n<p>While enhanced access to STARS data represents added value for AASHE members and STARS participants, we also encourage broad research that advances sustainability across the spectrum. For this reason, individuals conducting sustainability research who do not currently have access to STARS data displays may complete this form to request temporary access.</p>\r\n<p><span>Who should complete this form?</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>If your institution is not a STARS participant but is an AASHE member, you may complete this form to request temporary access to the Score Display.</li>\r\n<li>If your institution is not a STARS participant or an AASHE member, you may complete this form to request temporary access to the Category Display, Score Display, and Content Display.</li>\r\n<li>If your institution is a STARS participant, you already have access to all of the STARS data displays. You do not need to complete this form. To learn more about how the STARS data displays can help you with conducting research,&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/data_display_tips.pdf\" target=\"_self\">click here</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Full access to the STARS data displays is just one of the many benefits of participating in STARS. Before completing this form, we encourage members of your institution to consider the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-participant-benefits.html\" target=\"_blank\">benefits of participating in STARS</a>.</p>\r\n<p><em>In submitting this form, you indicate that you have read, understood, and are willing to comply with the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/data_use_guidelines.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">STARS Data Use Guidelines</a>.</em></p>');
