VALUES
	(3,'Help',1,'<p>For answers to general questions &ndash;  including questions about participation logistics, ratings, and reporting &ndash; visit <a href=\"/pages/faqs/?root_category=about\" target=\"_self\">STARS FAQs</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Not sure where to start with STARS? Visit the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/help/getting-started/\" target=\"_self\">Getting Started Help Page</a>.</p>\r\n<p>To pose a question to the campus sustainability community (including AASHE staff and other STARS Participants), post your question to AASHE\'s <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/forums\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Discussion Forums</a>.  You may wish to search the Forums to see if it someone has already raised the same question.</p>\r\n<p>For information about AASHE, the organization that developed and administers STARS, visit the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/about/about.php\" target=\"_self\">About AASHE</a>, <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/about/faq.php\" target=\"_self\">AASHE FAQs</a>, or the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/about/contact.php\" target=\"_self\">Contact Information</a> pages.</p>\r\n<p>To connect with the STARS Team directly, email <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> or call (303) 395-1332.</p>',0,'help','2013-09-13 11:58:35'),
	(0,'Overview',2,'<p>The Sustainability Tracking, Assessment &amp; Rating System&trade; (STARS) is a transparent, self-reporting framework for colleges and universities to measure their sustainability performance.  STARS&reg; was developed by <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">AASHE</a>, an acknowledged thought leader that advances sustainability by providing invaluable resources, with broad participation from diverse representatives of the higher education community.</p>\r\n<p>STARS is designed to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Provide a framework for understanding sustainability in all sectors of higher education.</li>\r\n<li>Enable meaningful comparisons over time and across institutions using a common set of measurements developed with broad participation from the campus sustainability community.</li>\r\n<li>Create incentives for continual improvement toward sustainability.</li>\r\n<li>Facilitate information sharing about higher education sustainability practices and performance.</li>\r\n<li>Build a stronger, more diverse campus sustainability community.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The STARS framework is intended to engage and recognize the full spectrum of colleges and universities &ndash; from community colleges to research universities, and from institutions just starting their sustainability programs to long-time campus sustainability leaders. STARS encompasses long-term sustainability goals for already high-achieving institutions as well as entry points of recognition for institutions that are taking first steps toward sustainability.</p>\r\n<h2>Eligibility</h2>\r\n<p>Any college or university located in the United States or Canada may <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/4269/?root_category=get-involved\" target=\"_self\">register to participate in STARS</a>.  International institutions are welcome to participate in the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-international-pilot.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS International Pilot</a>.</p>\r\n<p>STARS provides a framework for institutions taking first steps toward  sustainability as well as for established sustainability leaders. An  institution is defined by having a separate and distinct administration  (e.g. president or chancellor). For an institution which may be a part  of a larger system, it must have an administration that is separate and  distinct from others in the system of which it is a part in order to  register for STARS.</p>\r\n<p>If an institution or entity does not meet these requirements but has a compelling case for participating in STARS, the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/cfm/eligibility-inquiry/\" target=\"_self\">Eligibility Inquiry Form</a> may be submitted to petition to register for STARS. The form will be  evaluated by the STARS staff, who will decide if the institution or  entity is eligible to participate in STARS.</p>\r\n<h2>STARS Brochure &amp; Flyer</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/screen_shot_2012-05-23_at_9.00.34_am.png\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" align=\"left\" />The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_brochure_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Brochure</a> (pdf) and <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_flyer_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Flyer</a> (pdf) are documents created by AASHE with the intention of sharing a brief snapshot of the STARS Program including benefits and how the program works.&nbsp; Both resources may be shared with your colleagues, community members, and campus to communicate information about the STARS Program.</p>\r\n<p>The STARS Flyer is a one-page document while the STARS Brochure is a two-page document where each page is intended to be printed back-to-back on a single sheet of paper and folded.&nbsp; Please see the STARS Brochure <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/flyer_brochure_instructions_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">printing instructions</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h2>STARS Overview Presentation&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/screen_shot_2012-05-23_at_9.01.41_am.png\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p>The STARS&nbsp;Overview     Presentation (<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview_presentation.pptx\" target=\"_self\">ppt</a> | <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview_presentation.pdf\" target=\"_self\">pdf</a>)  highlights the details of the  STARS&nbsp;program.&nbsp;   Use this resource to  share information about the STARS&nbsp;program with  your  institution.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>About AASHE</h2>\r\n<p><br /><img src=\"https://stars.aashe.org/media/static//images/AASHE_RGB_72.png\" border=\"0\" alt=\"AASHE Logo\" hspace=\"5\" vspace=\"0\" width=\"250\" align=\"left\" />STARS is a program of AASHE, the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">Association for the Advancement of Sustainability in Higher Education</a>.  AASHE is a <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/membership/description.php\" target=\"_self\">member-driven organization</a> with a mission to empower higher education to lead the sustainability transformation.  <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/about/about.php\" target=\"_self\">Learn more about AASHE</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>AASHE has launched a new brand!&nbsp; Learn what this means for <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/introducing_the_new_aashe_brand_for_stars_institutions.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Institutions</a> (pdf).</p>',0,'about','2013-09-13 11:58:35'),
	(1,'Get Involved',3,'<p>STARS is a highly collaborative project.  AASHE offers several opportunities for engagement with STARS.  Participation from all stakeholders is welcome.</p>\r\n<h2>Register for STARS</h2>\r\n<p>Earn recognition for sustainability leadership by registering as a STARS Participant today.  <a href=\"/pages/get-involved/4269/?root_category=get-involved\" target=\"_self\">Learn more about registration</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Provide Feedback</h2>\r\n<p>Feedback on STARS is welcome at all times. Please send suggestions and comments to <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_blank\">stars@aashe.org</a> at any time. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Attend STARS Events</h2>\r\n<p>Check out the following STARS events, trainings, and sessions to learn more about the program. &nbsp;For information about webinars, visit the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/events/webinars\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Webinars webpage</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://conference.aashe.org/2013/\" target=\"_self\">AASHE 2013: Resiliency &amp; Adaptation</a><br /> Oct. 6 - 9 | Nashville, TN</p>\r\n<h2>Participate in STARS Governance</h2>\r\n<p>The STARS governance structure includes the STARS Steering Committee, Technical Advisors, Partner Organizations, and AASHE&rsquo;s Board of Directors. <a href=\"http://stars.aashe.org/pages/governance/?root_category=about\" target=\"_self\">Learn more about governance</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Engage in STARS as a Student</h2>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/students-and-stars.html\" target=\"_self\">\"Students and STARS\"</a> webpage provides several tips and resources to assist students participating in STARS on their campus, or those that are seeking to register their institution for the STARS Program.</p>\r\n<h2>Campus Sustainability Data Collector</h2>\r\n<p>Since March 2011, the Association for the Advancement of Sustainability  in Higher Education (AASHE), The Princeton Review, Sierra magazine, and  the Sustainable Endowments Institute has been collaborating on an effort  to streamline the reporting process for institutions that choose to  participate in various higher education sustainability assessments. The  intent of this initiative is to streamline the reporting process and  reduce the amount of time campus staff spend completing related surveys. The result is the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/campus-sustainability-data-collector/\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability  Data Collector</a>.</p>',0,'get-involved','2013-09-13 11:58:35'),
	(2,'News & Events',4,'<h2>News</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Announcements</strong></p>\r\n<p><a href=\" http://www.aashe.org/highlights/press-releases/aashe-finds-its-voice-new-brand-strategy\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Finds Its Voice with New Brand Strategy</a> (5.23.12)</p>\r\n<p><span><a href=\"http://greenreportcard.org/media\" target=\"_self\">New Focus at Sustainable Endowments Institute</a> (4.1.12)</span></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/highlights/press-releases/aashe-streamlines-campus-sustainability-survey-data-collection\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Streamlines Campus Sustainability Survey Data Collection</a> (1.31.12)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/highlights/press-releases/stars-ratings-pass-100-institution-mark\" target=\"_self\">STARS Ratings Pass 100 Institution Mark</a> (8.4.11)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/highlights/press-releases/aashe-releases-stars-year-review\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Releases \'STARS: A Year in Review\'</a> (4.14.11)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/highlights/press-releases/stars-recognizes-new-submissions\" target=\"_self\">STARS Recognizes New Submissions</a> (2.1.11)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Press%20Release.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">AASHE Launches STARS 1.0, the Nation&rsquo;s First Comprehensive Sustainability Rating System for Colleges and Universities</a> (1.19.10)</p>\r\n<p><strong>Media Coverage</strong><br /> Featured articles listed below. <a href=\"http://www.insidehighered.com/news/2010/07/20/green\" target=\"_blank\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></a>View a complete list of current <a href=\"/pages/news-events/4178/?root_category=news-events\" target=\"_blank\">STARS media coverage</a> or view the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/media-archive.html\" target=\"_self\">media archive</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/iau_horizons_vol__18_n_2_en_internet.pdf\" target=\"_self\"><strong>STARS - An AASHE Assessment Initiative</strong></a><br /><em>IAU Horizons </em>(Jun. 2012)</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://chronicle.com/blogs/buildings/colleges-make-their-debut-in-new-green-rating-system/28686\" target=\"_self\"><strong>Colleges Make Their Debut in New Green-Rating System</strong></a><strong>&nbsp;</strong><br /><em>Chronicle of Higher Education </em>(Feb. 1, 2011)</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/SCUP_Viewpoint_1.1.11.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Viewpoint</a></strong></span><br /><em>SCUP&nbsp;</em>(Jan. 2011)</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"text-decoration: underline;\"><strong><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/SCUP_STARS_1.1.11.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS</a></strong></span><br /><em>SCUP&nbsp;</em>(Jan. 2011)</p>\r\n<h2>AASHE Newsletters</h2>\r\n<p>For the latest news, articles, resources, participant highlights, events, and more about STARS and other issues related to sustainability in higher education, subscribe to one or all of the AASHE newsletters. <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/connect/enewsletters\" target=\"_self\">Subscribe today</a>!</p>\r\n<p>Please note: to subscribe you must have an <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/user/register\" target=\"_blank\">AASHE Account</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Events</h2>\r\n<p>Check out the following STARS&nbsp;events, trainings, and sessions to learn more about the program. &nbsp;For information about webinars, visit the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/events/webinars\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Webinars webpage</a>.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://conference.aashe.org/2013/\" target=\"_self\">AASHE 2013: Resiliency &amp; Adaptation</a><br />Oct. 6 - 9 | Nashville, TN</p>',0,'news-events','2013-09-13 11:58:35'),
