INSERT INTO `old_cms_newarticle` (`ordinal`, `title`, `created`, `id`, `content`, `published`, `slug`, `teaser`, `irc_id`, `timestamp`)
VALUES
	(100,'How to Use the STARS Reporting Tool','2009-11-04 20:42:18',1,'<h2>Step 1: Log in</h2>\r\n<p>To access the STARS&nbsp;Reporting Tool, <a href=\"/auth/login/\" target=\"_self\">log in</a> to the STARS website by entering your email address and password associated with your AASHE Account (i.e., the account you use to access AASHE&rsquo;s Resource Center). If you have lost or forgotten your AASHE password, you may <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/user/password\" target=\"_self\">re-set it here</a>.  If you do not have an AASHE Account, you may <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/user/register\" target=\"_self\">create one here</a>.</p>\r\n<p>Please note: only the individual who registered the institution will be able to log in initially.  To grant additional users access to the Tool, the individual who registered the institution should log in, choose the \"Manage Institution\" link, and click on the \"Users\" tab.</p>\r\n<h2>Step 2:&nbsp; Access the Reporting Tool</h2>\r\n<p>Follow the <a href=\"/tool/\" target=\"_self\">Reporting Tool link</a> at the top right of the STARS&nbsp;website to get started.</p>\r\n<h2>Step 3: Enter Data</h2>\r\n<p>To begin entering data, select &ldquo;<a href=\"/tool/submissions/\" target=\"_self\">My Submission</a>&rdquo; from the menu.&nbsp; This takes you to a summary page that provides an overview of your progress.  From the summary page, you may select the category or credit for which you&rsquo;d like to begin entering information.</p>\r\n<h2>Step 4: Submit for a Rating</h2>\r\n<p>Once you have completed entering data into the Reporting Tool you may submit the data for a STARS&nbsp;rating.&nbsp; Under \"<a href=\"/tool/submissions/\" target=\"_self\">My Submission</a>\" select \"<a href=\"/tool/submissions/submit/\" target=\"_self\">Submit for a Rating</a>\" in the status table on the top of the page.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For additional resources on using the STARS&nbsp;Reporting Tool, please see the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/stars-webinars/2010-stars-webinars.html#feb2010\" target=\"_self\"><em>STARS Reporting Tool 101</em> webinar archive.</a></p>',0,'how-to-use-the-stars-reporting-tool','<h2>Step 1: Log in</h2>',3900,'2012-07-05 11:05:23'),
	(0,'How should I provide feedback?','2009-11-05 11:56:23',2,'<p>There are three main avenues for providing feedback:</p>\r\n<p>1)&nbsp; AASHE would appreciate responses to any or all of the questions outlined <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Beta_Testers_Questions.doc\">in this document</a> (doc)&nbsp;by Monday, November 23.</p>\r\n<p>2)&nbsp; Throughout the testing process, please share any thoughts, concerns, and suggestions with AASHE by emailing stars@aashe.org.</p>\r\n<p>3)&nbsp; A survey will be given at the end of the Beta Testing period to capture final thoughts and feedback.</p>',1,'how-should-i-provide-feedback','<p>There are three main avenues for providing feedback:</p>\r\n<p>1)&nbsp; AASHE would appreciate responses to any or all of the questions outlined <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Beta_Testers_Questions.doc\">in this document</a> (doc)&nbsp;by Monday, November 23.</p>',3906,'2010-12-08 21:01:50'),
	(0,'When does the Beta Testing period conclude?','2009-11-05 12:15:29',3,'<p>Providing feedback early will allow AASHE time to incorporate suggestions and changes to the site before launching the tool widely in January.&nbsp; With that in mind, please provide responses to <a href=\"/files/documents/STARS/Beta_Testers_Questions.doc\">these questions</a> by November 23. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The Beta testing period will run through January 11, 2010. At that time, this site will close and you will not be able to enter additional data until the Reporting Tool launches widely later that month. Although additional data will not be able to be entered after January 11, 2010, you may still submit feedback to STARS on the Reporting Tool.</p>',1,'when-does-the-beta-testing-period-conclude','<p>Providing feedback early will allow AASHE time to incorporate suggestions and changes to the site before launching the tool widely in January.&nbsp; With that in mind, please provide responses to <a href=\"/files/documents/STARS/Beta_Testers_Questions.doc\">these questions</a> by November 23. &nbsp;</p>',3908,'2010-12-08 21:01:50'),
	(0,'What should I look for?  What am I testing?','2009-11-05 12:19:17',4,'<p>As a Beta Tester, you will have an opportunity to enter data into the STARS Reporting Tool and provide AASHE with feedback on how to make the tool easy to use.&nbsp; This includes spotting any errors or bugs with the site and making recommendations for how to improve the overall experience.&nbsp; </p>\r\n<p>Although fabricated data are acceptable during the testing period, we encourage Beta Testers to get started with their actual submission and use real data. Data submitted during the Beta testing period will carry over in your account when the Reporting Tool launches in January.</p>\r\n<p>AASHE will continue building the Reporting Tool and fixing bugs during this period, so the look of the site and minor features may change. We\'ll keep you updated if there are any additional changes you should know about throughout the Beta Testing phase. </p>',1,'what-should-i-look-for-what-am-i-testing','<p>As a Beta Tester, you will have an opportunity to enter data into the STARS Reporting Tool and provide AASHE with feedback on how to make the tool easy to use.&nbsp; This includes spotting any errors or bugs with the site and making recommendations for how to improve the overall experience.&nbsp; </p>',3909,'2010-12-08 21:01:50'),
	(300,'Historic Documents','2009-12-02 11:53:49',5,'<!--break-->\r\n<p>Before launching <a href=\"hhttps://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\"></a>the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">current version of STARS</a>, AASHE released several earlier drafts for public comment.  Key documents from throughout the STARS development process are posted below.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>STARS&nbsp;1.0 <br /> </strong></h2>\r\n<p>AASHE&nbsp;launched the STARS&nbsp;1.0 Early Release in September 2009. While the credits included in this version are the same as are included in STARS 1.0, AASHE made minor administrative updates after releasing this document and releasing STARS 1.0 in January 2010.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_1.0_Early_Release_Technical_Manual.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS&nbsp;1.0 Early Release Technical Manual </a>(pdf)<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/stars/early-release\" target=\"_self\"><br /> </a></li>\r\n<li>The STARS&nbsp;Technical Manual <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Technical_Manual_Changes.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Record of Changes</a> (pdf) details the minor differences between the Early Release edition and the January 2010 updated edition.&nbsp;</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>AASHE&nbsp;released STARS 1.0 in January 2010.&nbsp; Again, the credits included in this edition of the Technical Manual are the same as the latest version, but AASHE issued an Administrative Update to the system in June 2010 and November 2011.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_1.0_Technical_Manual.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS 1.0 Technical Manual </a>(January 2010 edition) (pdf)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_1.0_Admin_Update_One.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Record of Changes</a> (pdf) details the changes between the January 2010 and June 2010 edition</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/STARS_1.0.1_Technical_Manual.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS 1.0 Technical Manual</a> (June 2010 edition) (pdf)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/1.0.2_Record_of_Changes_05Nov10.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Record of Changes</a> (pdf) details the changes between the June 2010 and November 2010 edition.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong> STARS Pilot Project</strong></h2>\r\n<p>The STARS pilot project took place from February 2008 to January 2009 and involved <a href=\"http://stars.aashe.org/pages/history/4597/?root_category=about#Institutions_Participating_in_the_STARS_Pilot\" target=\"_self\">66 institutions</a> in the US&nbsp;and Canada.&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Pilot_Phase_One_Guide.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Guide to Pilot Phase One</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Pilot_Phase_Two.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Guide to Pilot Phase Two</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Pilot_Results_0.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Pilot Project Results</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://stars.aashe.org/pages/history/4597/?root_category=about#STARS_Pilot_Project_Conference_Calls_\" target=\"_self\">Notes from conference calls about the pilot project</a><strong><br /> </strong></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>STARS 0.5</strong></h2>\r\n<p>AASHE released STARS 0.5 in April 2008.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_0.5.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS 0.5</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/documents/stars/STARS_0.5_Feedback.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Feedback on STARS 0.5</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>STARS 0.4</strong></h2>\r\n<p>AASHE released STARS 0.4 in September 2007.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS0.4.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS 0.4</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS0.4commentsv2.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Comments on STARS 0.4</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS0.4_survey_responses.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Responses to STARS 0.4 Survey</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://stars.aashe.org/pages/history/4599\" target=\"_self\">Notes from conference calls about STARS 0.4</a></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong> Predecessors of STARS</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/CSRS_0.1.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Rating System (CSRS) 0.1</a> (pdf) - released January 2007</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/CSRSproposal.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Original Campus Sustainability Rating System Proposal</a> (pdf) - released January 2007</li>\r\n<li class=\"spaced_list\">Sustainability in Higher Education Assessment Framework (SHEAF) - a 2006 project that grew to become STARS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Summary Notes from Conference Workshops</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/SSCC07_workshop_summary.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Smart and Sustainable Campuses Conference</a> (pdf) - April 2007</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/RMSS_workshop_summary.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Rocky Mountain Sustainability Summit</a> (pdf) - Feb. 2007</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><strong>Other Documents</strong></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Governance_Structure.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS&nbsp;Governance Structure</a> (pdf) - Jan. 2010</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/HEASCcall.pdf\" target=\"_self\">HEASC Call for a Campus Sustainability Rating System</a> (pdf) - Aug. 2006<a href=\"STARS_intro.ppt\" target=\"_self\"><br /> </a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.net/staffblog/campus-operations/podcast-all-about-stars\" target=\"_self\">Listen to the STARS&nbsp;podcast</a> (18 minutes) -- Feb. 2008</li>\r\n</ul>',0,'historic-documents','<p>View key documents from the STARS development process, including previous draft versions and feedback received.</p>',4100,'2013-08-08 10:14:20'),
	(100,'Steering Committee','2009-11-12 16:51:56',6,'<p>The STARS Steering Committee is comprised of campus representatives, members of the AASHE Board of Directors, and AASHE&nbsp;Staff.&nbsp; STARS&nbsp;Steering Committee members advise on program policy, finances, and strategic positioning, in addition to reviewing and approving updates and revisions to the technical content of STARS, including each new version.&nbsp; View the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_governance_structure.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS&nbsp;Governance Structure</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h2>Steering Committee Members</h2>\r\n<p><em>Campus Representatives<br /> </em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Julian Dautremont-Smith</strong> - Chief Sustainability Officer, Alfred State College</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jeremy Friedman -</strong>Manager, Sustainability Initiatives, New York University</p>\r\n<p><strong>Elaine Hanson</strong> - Director, Office for Sustainability, Sheridan College</p>\r\n<p><strong>Preston Jacobsen</strong> - Sustainability Analyst, Haywood Community College</p>\r\n<p><strong>Nurit Katz - </strong><span>Chief Sustainability Officer</span>, University of California, Los Angeles<strong><br /></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>H. Scott Matthews </strong>- Faculty and Research Director, Carnegie Mellon University<br /><strong></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong>Chris O\'Brien</strong> - Director of Sustainability, American University</p>\r\n<p><strong>Stephenie Presseller</strong> - Sustainability Manager, Moraine Valley Community College</p>\r\n<p><strong>Cindy Shea</strong> - Director, Sustainability Office, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill</p>\r\n<p><em>AASHE&nbsp;Board Members&nbsp;</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>William Brown </strong>- Director of Sustainability,&nbsp; Indiana University</p>\r\n<p><strong>Jon Jensen</strong> - Director of Environmental Studies, Luther College</p>\r\n<p><strong>Dave Newport</strong> - Director, Environmental Center, University of Colorado at Boulder</p>\r\n<p><em>AASHE Staff</em></p>\r\n<p><strong>Meghan Fay Zahniser</strong> - Director of Programs, AASHE</p>\r\n<p><strong>Paul Rowland </strong>- Executive Director, AASHE<strong><br /> </strong></p>\r\n<p>View the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/2013_sc_bios_pics.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Steering Committee Members\' bios</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h2>Roles and Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<p>STARS Steering Committee Members:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Advise on STARS policy, finances, and strategic positioning in response to proposals from staff and other Committee Members and make recommendations to the AASHE Board of Directors and STARS staff as necessary. For example, the Steering Committee may be asked to provide feedback on topics such as educational offerings, revenue opportunities, partnerships or other activities related to the success of the program.</li>\r\n<li>Review and approve updates and revisions to the technical content of STARS, including each new version.</li>\r\n<li>Determine the appropriate course of action when a submission is contested and the issue cannot be resolved by staff.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The committee generally meets once a month by conference call and in-person as needed. Members are expected to attend calls and contribute sufficient time to address the continued development and strategic positioning of STARS. Members receive no remuneration for their services.</p>\r\n<h2>Meeting Notes and Supporting Documents<em><br /> </em></h2>\r\n<p>July 19, 2013</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_sc_mtg_minutes_7.19.13.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Meeting Notes</a>&nbsp;(pdf)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_data_accuracy_policy_07.19.13_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Data Accuracy Policy</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>June 21, 2013</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_steering_committee_meeting_6.21.13.pdf\" target=\"_self\">M