ef=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Correcting%20Mistakes%20in%20the%20Reporting%20Tool_0.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Correcting Mistakes in the Reporting Tool Proposal</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>March 25, 2010</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%20Steering%20Committee%20Meeting%203.25.10%20FINAL.pdf\" target=\"_self\"> Meeting Notes</a> (pdf)<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%20Outreach%20Update%203.18.pdf\" target=\"_self\"><br /> </a></li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Technical%20Advisors%20Proposal_0.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Technical Advisors Proposal</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>February 12, 2010</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%20Steering%20Committee%20Meeting%202.12.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Meeting Notes</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>',0,'steering-committee','<p>The STARS Steering Committee is comprised of campus representatives, members of the AASHE Board of Directors, and AASHE&nbsp;Staff.&nbsp; STARS&nbsp;Steering Committee members advise on program policy, finances, and strategic positioning, in addition to reviewing and approving updates and revisions to the technical content of STARS, including each new version. &nbsp;<a href=\"http://www\" target=\"_self\"></a></p>',3971,'2013-08-01 09:29:57'),
	(300,'Technical Advisors','2009-11-12 17:05:20',7,'<p>AASHE seeks individuals with expertise related to campus sustainability to serve as STARS Technical Advisors. STARS Technical Advisors are the primary source for input and insight regarding the content of STARS credits. Technical Advisors are drawn from higher education institutions, non-profit organizations, and businesses, with preference given for AASHE members. Individuals nominated by STARS Partner Organizations&nbsp;are given special consideration during the selection process.</p>\r\n<p>Technical Advisors should possess:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>A desire and ability to contribute to the success of STARS</li>\r\n<li>A strong expertise in at least one content area covered in STARS</li>\r\n<li>Effective communication skills and the ability to work well on a team</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Meet the current <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_tas.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Technical Advisors</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h2>Roles and Responsibilities</h2>\r\n<p>AASHE appoints up to five Technical Advisors per STARS subcategory.</p>\r\n<p>Technical Advisors may spend five to ten&nbsp;hours per month to STARS, though less time will be required during a typical month. The time required to serve as a Technical Advisor will vary based on two main factors:</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li>The volume and nature of the technical questions AASHE receives -- For example, if AASHE receives several credit interpretation requests and technical questions related to the Transportation credits in one month, those Technical Advisors would be called upon more regularly. If no credit interpretation requests or technical questions are raised (which is typical for most subcategories most months), Technical Advisors may not be called upon at all that month.</li>\r\n<li>The phase of the STARS revision cycle -- During periods when AASHE is actively working on preparing new draft credits for public review or testing, Technical Advisors will have more responsibilities than during periods of maintenance.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>Technical Advisors generally work to resolve substantive issues as a sub-category group. Depending on the issue in question, Technical Advisors may be asked to provide written suggestions or responses by email or to participate in telephone calls.</p>\r\n<p>The credit revision process begins by consulting with Technical Advisors in that topic area.</p>\r\n<h2>Selection and Terms</h2>\r\n<p>Up to five Technical Advisors per STARS sub-category are selected and appointed by the STARS Steering Committee, based on the criteria outlined above. In addition, Technical Advisors are selected to reflect the diversity of higher education institutions.</p>\r\n<p>Technical Advisors are appointed for a term of three years. There are no limits to the number of times an Advisor may be re-appointed.</p>\r\n<h2>Technical Advisor Orientation Webinar</h2>\r\n<p>&nbsp;You may view the STARS Technical Advisor Orientation webinar here.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"425\" height=\"344\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/IGi1G7Vv00c?hl=en&amp;fs=1\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"425\" height=\"344\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/IGi1G7Vv00c?hl=en&amp;fs=1\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>',0,'technical-advisors','<p>AASHE seeks individuals with expertise related to campus sustainability to serve as STARS Technical Advisors. STARS Technical Advisors are the primary source for input and insight regarding the content of STARS credits. Technical Advisors are drawn from higher education institutions, non-profit organizations, and businesses, with preference given for AASHE members.</p>',3973,'2013-08-01 09:34:17'),
	(400,'STARS Partner Organizations','2009-11-13 10:23:23',8,'<p>STARS Partner Organizations are higher education associations and other non-profit organizations that provide value to the development and promotion of STARS. These organizations work to educate their constituents about STARS and engage them in its ongoing refinement and development. More information about the roles and responsibilities of Partner Organizations is included in the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_governance_structure.pdf\" target=\"_self\"> STARS Governance Structure</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<p>Partner Organizations enjoy the following benefits:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>At  opportunity to nominate a member, constituent, or staff person to serve as a Technical Advisor to STARS</li>\r\n<li>Recognition on the STARS website and in the STARS Technical Manual</li>\r\n<li>Access to materials to help educate their members and constituents about STARS</li>\r\n<li>Frequent communications with STARS staff that provide an opportunity to give direct feedback on the program</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Please email  <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> to inquire about becoming a STARS&nbsp;Partner Organization.</p>\r\n<h2>Partner Organizations</h2>\r\n<p>AASHE would also like to appreciate our Partner Organizations. Please email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>&nbsp;to inquire about becoming a STARS Partner Organization.</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://www.acuho-i.org/?tabid=125\" target=\"_self\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/acuhoi_horiz_0.jpg\" border=\"0\" width=\"322\" height=\"116\" /></a>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www2.aashe.org/heasc/\" target=\"_self\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/HEASClogo_green_WEB.jpg\" border=\"0\" width=\"210\" height=\"60\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=