d in sustainability assessment, strongest performer in PAC-12</a><br />Nov. 21, 2012</p>\r\n<p class=\"contentheading\"><a href=\"http://newsletter.blogs.wesleyan.edu/2012/11/15/stars/\" target=\"_self\">Wesleyan to Gauge Sustainability Efforts with Assessment System</a><br />Nov. 15, 2012</p>\r\n<p class=\"contentheading\"><a href=\"http://www.usustatesman.com/usu-registers-with-a-new-sustainability-rating-system-1.2787405#.UJfXUWl24Sw\" target=\"_self\">USU registers with a new sustainability program</a><br />Nov. 1, 2012</p>\r\n<p class=\"contentheading\"><a href=\"http://surfky.com/index.php/communities/54-local-hopkinsville-top-news/20401-hcc-registers-as-first-kctcs-participant-in-sustainability-rating-system\" target=\"_self\">HCC Registers as First KCTCS Participant in Sustainability Rating System</a><br /> Sept. 28, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://now.uiowa.edu/2012/09/regents-schools-join-sustainability-rating-system\" target=\"_self\">Regents schools join sustainability rating system</a><br /> Sept. 14, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://newscenter.iupui.edu/5773/IUPUI-to-measure-sustainability-performance-of-campus\" target=\"_self\">IUPUI to measure sustainability performance on campus</a><br /> Sept. 12, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.pbn.com/Bryant-U-receives-STARS-bronze-rating-for-sustainability-efforts,70257\" target=\"_self\">Bryant U. receives STARS bronze rating for sustainability efforts</a><br /> Sept. 5, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ia.ucsb.edu/pa/display.aspx?pkey=2786\" target=\"_self\">UC Santa Barbara Ranks Among Top U.S. Universities in STARS Sustainability Ratings </a><br /> Jul. 19, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://news.csumb.edu/news/2012/jul/11/csumb-lauded-innovations-sustainability\" target=\"_self\">CSUMB lauded for \'innovations\' in sustainability</a><br /> Jul. 11, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://news.stanford.edu/thedish/?p=20095\" target=\"_self\">Stanford earns gold rating for sustainability efforts</a><br /> Jul. 3, 2012</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://news.wfu.edu/2012/06/06/media-advisory-wfu-receives-silver-rating-from-stars-sustainability-assessment/\" target=\"_self\">WFU receives Silver rating from STARS Sustainability Assessment</a><br /> Jun. 6, 2012</p>',1,'media-coverage','',4178,'2013-08-08 16:06:00'),
	(199,'2012 Publications','2012-04-03 10:57:27',84,'<h2>STARS Quarterly Review</h2>\r\n<p>In 2012, AASHE published STARS data in a quarterly format, through the STARS Quarterly Review (SQR). Each edition of the SQR tells a story of sustainability in higher education based on data submitted in STARS Reports. AASHE expects to publish an annual STARS report in late-summer 2013. For questions, comments, or to submit thoughts and ideas for upcoming STARS publications, please email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"fall2012\" target=\"_self\"></a><a name=\"winter2012\" target=\"_self\"></a>WINTER 2012</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_winter_2012-final.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS Quarterly Review: Winter 2012\" onclick=\"_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\', \'Publications\', \'Download\', \'STARS Quarterly Review Winter 2012\']);\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_winter_2012-cover_final.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Winter 2012 SQR cover\" width=\"259\" height=\"335\" align=\"left\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_winter_2012-final.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Winter SQR\">Winter 2012 SQR</a>:&nbsp;<em>Recap &amp; A Look Ahead</em>,&nbsp;reviews recent developments related to the evolving concept of global campus sustainability and introduces changes that can be expected for STARS in 2013.</p>\r\n<p>Universidad de Monterrey (Mexico) is highlighted as the first STARS International Pilot participant to submit a STARS report and earn a rating. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>As STARS matures, more institutions are submitting multiple reports and using STARS as a tool for continuous improvement. Four institutions have been highlighted for recent advancements and initiatives identified in their most recent STARS reports.</p>\r\n<p>Closing out the year, this edition looks at changes that can be expected for STARS in 2013, with descriptions of new credits proposed for the launch of STARS 2.0 slated for release in 2013.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"fall2012\" target=\"_self\"></a>FALL 2012</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_fall_2012-final.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS Quarterly Review: Fall 2012\" onclick=\"_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\', \'Publications\', \'Download\', \'STARS Quarterly Review Fall 2012\']);\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_fall_2012-cover_final.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Fall 2012 SQR cover\" width=\"259\" height=\"335\" align=\"left\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_fall_2012-final.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"Fall SQR\">Fall 2012 SQR</a>:&nbsp;<em>The Role of Institutional Diversity</em>,&nbsp;explores how the diversity of STARS institutions has changed over time and how participation in STARS according to institution type compares to U.S. demographics. Findings in this review suggest that the institutional characteristics that make higher education institutions distinct also play a role in how campuses are advancing sustainability.&nbsp;Particularly compelling is how NCAA conference rivalry is furthering sustainability on campuses.&nbsp;With 6 institutions highlighted,&nbsp;this&nbsp;issue covers data from reports submitted through September 1, 2012. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"summer2012\" target=\"_self\"></a>Summer 2012</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_summer_2012-final.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS Quarterly Review: Summer 2012\" onclick=\"_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\', \'Publications\', \'Download\', \'STARS Quarterly Review Summer 2012\']);\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_summer_2012-cover.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Summer 2012 SQR cover\" width=\"259\" height=\"335\" align=\"left\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_summer_2012-final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Summer 2012 SQR</a>: <em>Innovations in Campus Sustainability</em>, &nbsp;explores the critical linkages between education, innovation, and sustainability. &nbsp;This issue highlights new and ground-breaking practices within the Innovation (IN) category of STARS,&nbsp;focusing on the unique solutions within higher education that positively impact current and future generations. &nbsp; With 11 institutions highlighted,&nbsp;this&nbsp;issue covers data from reports submitted through June 1, 2012. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"spring2012\" target=\"_self\"></a>Spring 2012</h3>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_spring_2012_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS Quarterly Review: Spring 2012\" onclick=\"_gaq.push([\'_trackEvent\', \'Publications\', \'Download\', \'STARS Quarterly Review Spring 2012\']);\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_spring_2012-cover.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"Spring 2012 SQR cover\" width=\"259\" height=\"335\" align=\"left\" /></a></p>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sqr_spring_2012_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Spring 2012 SQR</a>: <em>Framing Campus Sustainability</em>,&nbsp;features stories that frame the evolving concept of sustainability in higher education. &nbsp;Included in this issue are a snapshot of ratings-to-date, a focus on credits within the Operations (OP) category, and insights into how institutions are defining and interpreting the evolving concepts of sustainability. &nbsp;Highlighting AASHE\'s direction of serving as a thought leader to advance sustainability, this issue covers data from reports submitted through March 1, 2012.</p>',0,'2012-publications','',NULL,'2013-08-01 09:33:09'),
	(140,'Using the STARS Logo and Seals','2012-06-05 08:55:09',85,'<p><a href=\"#how_visuals_affect_institution\" target=\"_self\">How do the STARS visuals affect my institution?</a><br /> <a href=\"#stars_seals\" target=\"_self\">Where can I find the STARS seals?</a><br /> <a href=\"#logo_use\" target=\"_self\">Can I use the STARS logo?</a><br /> <a href=\"#contact_info\" target=\"_self\">Who do I contact with questions about the AASHE brand?</a></p>\r\n<p><strong><a name=\"how_visuals_affect_institution\" target=\"_self\"></a>How do the STARS visuals affect my institution?</strong><br />AASHE encourages STARS Institutions, current STARS Participants as well as those that  have earned a rating, to prominently display the STARS seals in their publications, websites, and all  relevant promotional materials.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a name=\"stars_seals\" target=\"_self\"></a>Where can I find the STARS seals?</strong><br /> The STARS seals as well as the Brand Guidelines, a document that  outlines the appropriate use of the AASHE brand, is available  in the &ldquo;My Resources&rdquo; section of the STARS Reporting Tool.</p>\r\n<p><strong><a name=\"logo_use\" target=\"_self\"></a>Can I use the STARS logo?</strong><br /> If you are interested in using the STARS logo, please email <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> and explain why you\'re hoping to use the STARS logo and in what capacity.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"line-height: 1.5;\">Who do I contact with questions about the AASHE brand?</strong></p>\r\n<p>-&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Questions about STARS visuals, website or Reporting Tool, contact <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a><br /> -&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; All other questions about the new brand, contact <a href=\"mailto:info@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">info@aashe.org</a></p>',1,'new-improved-aashe-brand','<p><a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/new-improved-aashe-brand.html#why_new_logo\" target=\"_self\">Why did AASHE create a new logo and visual identity?</a><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/new-improved-aashe-brand.html#how_visuals_affect_institution\" target=\"_self\">How do the new AASHE and STARS visuals affect my institution?</a><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/new-improved-aashe-brand.html#stars_seals\" target=\"_self\">Where can I find the STARS seals?</a><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/new-improved-aashe-brand.html#logo_use\" target=\"_self\">Can I use the STARS logo?</a><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/new-improved-aashe-brand.html#changes\" target=\"_self\">What has changed with the new and improved AASHE brand and what will stay the same?</a><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/new-improved-aashe-brand.html#contact_info\" target=\"_self\">Who do I contact with questions about the new and improved AASHE brand?</a></p>',NULL,'2013-02-25 15:21:21'),
	(200,'Registration','2010-01-19 02:18:20',27,'<h2>Fees</h2>\r\n<p>All colleges and universities in the United States and Canada are welcome to participate in STARS and earn recognition for their sustainability initiatives.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"/register/\" target=\"_self\">Register today as a STARS Participant!</a></p>\r\n<p>STARS registration fees:<br /> AASHE Member...........................................$900<br /> Non-Member................................................$1,400</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<div class=\"im\">\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n</div>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Please note: in order to register for STARS, you must be logged in with your <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/accounts/help\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Account</a> (institutional email address and password).&nbsp; For more information about <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/membership\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Membership</a>, please visit the AASHE <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/\" target=\"_self\">website</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Discount for Renewing Participants</h2>\r\n<p>Institutions will have the opportunity to renew their participation with STARS at a 50% discount once their 12-months of access to the STARS Reporting Tool expires (i.e. $450 for AASHE members and $700 for non-members instead of $900 for AASHE members and $1,400 for non-members).&nbsp; This discount is only valid for institutions that renew their participation with STARS within 90 days of their previous subscription deadline. Institutions that renew their participation with STARS will gain an additional 12-months of access to the STARS Reporting Tool and will have the opportunity to update and save data documented as well as submit for a new STARS rating if they choose to do so.</p>\r\n<h2>Access to the STARS Reporting Tool</h2>\r\n<p>All registrants, both new and renewing, will have 12 months of   continuous access to the Reporting Tool. During this 12-month cycle,  institutions may submit a STARS  Report at any time. If an institution  submits before the 12th month, it will still  have access to the  Reporting Tool until the end of its cycle. With this  benefit of  continual access, no extensions will be given. Ongoing  access to the  STARS Reporting Tool will allow your institution to  maintain accurate  data even after a STARS Rating is achieved.<span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h2><span>Important Information<br /></span></h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>The fee is paid at the time of registration; there is not a separate submission fee.</li>\r\n<li>Institutions may pay by credit card online or select the &ldquo;pay later&rdquo; option and pay by check.  We can generate an invoice by request.  Institutions may access the STARS Reporting Tool once payment is received and a notification is sent.</li>\r\n<li>At registration, users will be asked for the name and contact information for your STARS Liaison as well as an executive-level administrator (president, vice president, provost, etc.) who will be included on an email regarding your institution&rsquo;s STARS registration.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><span><span>STARS Ratings<br /></span></span></h2>\r\n<p>A STARS rating is earned by institutions that have registered for  STARS and have gone through a comprehensive process of collecting and  publicly reporting information related to their sustainability  performance.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>An institution that wishes to participate in STARS but does not want to publish their score may participate as a <a href=\"/pages/about/faqs/ratings-and-credits.html#levels=about\" target=\"_self\">STARS Reporter</a>. These institutions receive the same benefits as institutions that pursue a STARS rating, including positive recognition for participation and the ability to share data publicly.  After seeing their final score, all participants are able to choose STARS Reporter status before completing their final submission and making it public.</p>\r\n<p>Have questions about participating?  <a href=\"/pages/faqs/4103/?root_category=about\" target=\"_self\">View STARS Participation FAQs</a>.</p>',0,'registration','<p>All colleges and universities in the United States and Canada are welcome to participate in STARS and earn recognition for their sustainability leadership.</p>\r\n<p>STARS participation fees:<br /> AASHE Member &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;$900<br /> Non-Member &hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;&hellip;.&hellip;&hellip;$1,400</p>',4269,'2013-07-30 12:41:38'),
	(600,'Students and STARS','2011-05-27 09:10:54',70,'<p>Are you a student that is interested in participating in STARS on your campus?&nbsp; Are you looking for information to encourage your institution to register for STARS?&nbsp; AASHE and STARS can support your involvement in the campus sustainability movement.&nbsp; This web page outlines several resources to get you started with STARS or enhance your current involvement in the program.&nbsp; <br /><br />Quick links to topics on this page:</p>\r\n<ol> </ol>\r\n<p><a href=\"#what_is_stars\" target=\"_self\">What is STARS?</a><br /> <a href=\"#why_stars\" target=\"_self\">Why is STARS important to students?</a><br /> <a href=\"#involved\" target=\"_self\">How can I get my institution involved in STARS?</a><br /> <a href=\"#connect_stakeholders\" target=\"_self\">How can I connect with campus stakeholders to share information about STARS?</a><br /> <a href=\"#stars_participant\" target=\"_self\">If my institution is a STARS Participant how can I be involved?</a><br /> <a href=\"#resources\" target=\"_self\">What helpful resources will help me stay engaged with AASHE and STARS?</a><br /><a href=\"#contact\" target=\"_self\">Who do I contact regarding questions about the STARS Program?</a></p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"what_is_stars\" target=\"_self\"></a>What is STARS?</h2>\r\n<p>View this informative video about the STARS Program that was created by students at the State University of New York at New Paltz.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"400\" height=\"225\">\r\n<param name=\"allowfullscreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" />\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=36434011&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\" /><embed type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"400\" height=\"225\" src=\"http://vimeo.com/moogaloop.swf?clip_id=36434011&amp;server=vimeo.com&amp;show_title=0&amp;show_byline=0&amp;show_portrait=0&amp;color=&amp;fullscreen=1&amp;autoplay=0&amp;loop=0\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"why_stars\" target=\"_self\"></a>Why is STARS important to students?</h2>\r\n<p>The Sustainability Tracking, Assessment &amp; Rating System&trade; (STARS) is a transparent, self-reporting framework for colleges and universities to measure their sustainability performance. Although it is important for campus administrators, faculty, and staff to be involved in the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/stars-webinars/2010-stars-webinars.html#jul2010\" target=\"_blank\">cross-campus collaboration</a> necessary to complete an institution&rsquo;s STARS Report, students have a great opportunity to be involved too.</p>\r\n<p>As a student participating in STARS through coursework, an independent project, an internship, as a volunteer, or even a paid employee, your involvement will provide you with valuable skills.&nbsp; Some of these skills may include: learning comprehensive data collection techniques, organizing disparate types of data and ways to conduct yourself in an interview or when working with campus stakeholders &ndash; all of which are valuable lessons that will be beneficial throughout your academic and professional careers.</p>\r\n<p>Even if your institution is a registered <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/institutions/\" target=\"_blank\">STARS Participant</a>, or not, this page will share information on the many ways for you to get involved.&nbsp;&nbsp; <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more</a> about the details of the STARS Program.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"involved\" target=\"_self\"></a>How can I get my institution involved in STARS?</h2>\r\n<p>As a student, there are several was you can encourage your institution to participate in the STARS Program.&nbsp; The first step is to determine if your institution is an <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/membership/members/institutional\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Member</a>.&nbsp; Then, contact campus stakeholders to discuss your institution&rsquo;s involvement in the STARS Program.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Ways to familiarize yourself with STARS:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Gather information on <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/registration.html\" target=\"_self\">registering</a> for the STARS Program.</li>\r\n<li>Review the STARS <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">Technical Manual</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Learn helpful details about STARS <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/reporting.html\" target=\"_self\">Reporting</a>, <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/rating.html\" target=\"_self\">Rating</a>, and <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/scoring.html\" target=\"_self\">Scoring</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Share the STARS <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/\" target=\"_self\">Governance Structure</a> with campus stakeholders.</li>\r\n<li>View a helpful <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/stars-webinars/2010-stars-webinars.html#aug2010\" target=\"_self\">webinar</a> on \"Achieving Administrative Support for STARS.\"</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"connect_stakeholders\" target=\"_self\"></a>How can I connect with campus stakeholders to share information about STARS?</h2>\r\n<p>Utilize these helpful email templates* when contacting campus stakeholders:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/introducing_stars_to_your_campus_administrators.doc\" target=\"_self\">Introducing STARS to Your Campus Administrators</a> (doc)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/encouraging_faculty_to_use_stars_in_courses.doc\" target=\"_self\">Encouraging Faculty to Use STARS in Courses</a> (doc)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>*<em>For institution\'s that are registered STARS Participants, additional email templates are available in the \"My Resources\" section of the STARS Reporting Tool.&nbsp; Please note, you must be listed as a \"user\" on your institution\'s STARS Report to access this information.&nbsp; Contact <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> for more information.</em></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2><a name=\"stars_participant\" target=\"_self\"></a>If my institution is a STARS Participant how can I be involved?</h2>\r\n<p>The STARS Liaison is the main contact regarding your institution&rsquo;s participation in the STARS Program.&nbsp; Reaching out to this individual is a great way to become involved with STARS on your campus.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Contact <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> if you are unaware of your institution&rsquo;s STARS Liaison.&nbsp; The STARS staff will be able to help you connect with this individual.</li>\r\n<li>Contact your institution&rsquo;s STARS Liaison, share your interest, and discuss your role.</li>\r\n<li>Learn <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/stars-webinars/2010-stars-webinars.html#apr2010\" target=\"_self\">how students are engaged</a> on other campuses.</li>\r\n<li>Become familiar with <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/news-events/stars-webinars/2010-stars-webinars.html#mar2010\" target=\"_self\">data collection strategies</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"resources\" target=\"_self\"></a>What helpful resources will help me stay engaged with AASHE and STARS?</h2>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/user/register\" target=\"_self\">Create</a> an AASHE account (Note: you do not have to be affiliated with an AASHE Member institution to create an AASHE account).</li>\r\n<li>Find valuable sustainability resources in the AASHE <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/resources\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Resource Center</a>.</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/connect/enewsletters\" target=\"_self\">Subscribe</a> to AASHE Newsletters.</li>\r\n<li>Participate in AASHE and STARS <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/events\" target=\"_self\">events</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Post on the AASHE <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/forums\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Discussion Forums</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Contribute to the AASHE Blog: <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/blog\" target=\"_self\">Campus Sustainability Perspectives</a>.</li>\r\n<li>Share the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview.ppt\" target=\"_self\">STARS Overview Presentation.</a> (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2><a name=\"contact\" target=\"_self\"></a>Who do I contact regarding questions about the STARS Program?</h2>\r\n<p>Submit your inquiries to <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> to connect with an AASHE Staff person about the STARS Program.</p>\r\n<p><em>See the &ldquo;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/connect/get-involved\" target=\"_self\">Get Involved</a>&rdquo; section of the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/\" target=\"_self\">AASHE website</a> to learn more ways to stay engaged with the campus sustainability community.</em></p>',0,'students-and-stars','',NULL,'2013-07-30 09:44:03'),
	(-2,'2012 STARS Webinars','2012-01-11 10:24:29',74,'<p>This page highlights the videos and presentations from monthly STARS   webinars throughout 2012.&nbsp; Click on the links below to be taken directly   to more information about the webinar listed. Please note the content  in the webinar was current when the webinar was  broadcast, but may  become outdated.&nbsp; Contact the STARS team, <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>, with any questions.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"#review\" target=\"_self\">2012: A Year in Review (Dec. 2012)</a><br /> <a href=\"#2.0_public_comment_period\" target=\"_self\">The STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period: &nbsp;An Overview (Oct. 2012)</a><br /> <a href=\"#innovation\" target=\"_self\">Highlighting Best Practices from the Innovation Category (Sept. 2012)</a><br /><a href=\"#human_resources\" target=\"_self\">Highlighting Best Practices from the Human Resources Sub-category (Aug. 2012)</a><br /> <a href=\"#energy\" target=\"_self\"><span class=\"regTextItem\">Highlighting Best Practices from the Energy Sub-category (Jun. 2012)</span></a><br /> <a href=\"#brand\" target=\"_self\">New and Improved AASHE Brand:  Where we were, where we&rsquo;re going, and what this means for STARS Institutions (May 2012)</a><br /> <a href=\"#curriculum_subcategory\" target=\"_self\">Highlighting Best Practices from the Curriculum Subcategory (Apr. 2012)</a><br /> <a href=\"#finalizing\" target=\"_self\">Finalizing a STARS Report in Record Time (Mar. 2012)</a><br /> <a href=\"#stars_1.2\" target=\"_self\">STARS 1.2 and Enhancements to the STARS Reporting Tool (Feb. 2012)<strong> </strong></a><br /> <strong>&nbsp;</strong><a href=\"#reducing_survey_fatigue\" target=\"_self\">Reducing Survey Fatigue: A Collaboration with AASHE, Sustainable Endowments Institute, the Princeton Review, and Sierra magazine (Feb. 2012)</a></p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"review\" target=\"_self\"></a>2012: A Year in Review</em></h2>\r\n<p>December is upon us and another year is coming to a close. What better time to reflect on all that we have learned over the past 12 months? This webinar was facilitated by AASHE Senior Programs Coordinator Jillian Buckholz on Tuesday, December 18 at 2 p.m. Eastern and gave an overview of developments in the STARS Program since January 2012. &nbsp;What to expect in 2013 was also highlighted.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/dec_webinar_ppt.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of the webinar content as presented by AASHE.</p>\r\n<p><iframe width=\"420\" height=\"315\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/PQmR1opU-8g\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"2.0_public_comment_period\" target=\"_self\"></a>The STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period: An Overview</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, October 30 at&nbsp;2 p.m. Eastern.</p>\r\n<p>In collaboration with the STARS Steering Committee, AASHE has finalized a draft of STARS 2.0. This draft version of the STARS Technical Manual will be available for public comment in the near future. View this webinar to learn more about the specific changes between STARS 1.2 and STARS 2.0, the details of participating in the public comment period, and next steps for STARS once feedback from the higher education community is received and reviewed by AASHE.</p>\r\n<p>The webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, Senior Programs Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Chris Pelton, Programs Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed presentation of the webinar content as presented by <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/oct_webinar_ppt.pdf\" target=\"_self\">AASHE</a> (pdf).&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><iframe width=\"420\" height=\"315\" src=\"http://www.youtube.com/embed/jqI3artNyAA\" frameborder=\"0\"></iframe></p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"innovation\" target=\"_self\"></a>Highlighting Best Practices from the Innovation Category</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, September 25 at&nbsp;2 p.m. Eastern.</p>\r\n<p>AASHE has learned that there are questions among the higher education community about what should be considered as innovative when documenting projects and programs for the Innovation Category of STARS. This webinar walked through the process of documenting an Innovation credit in the STARS Reporting Tool as well as highlight best practices in the Innovation Category by a rated STARS Institution.</p>\r\n<p>The webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Elaine Durr, Director of Sustainability, Elon University</li>\r\n<li>Deborah Long, Elon Academy Director and Professor of Education, Elon University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed presentation of the webinar content as presented by&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/sept_webinar_ppt.pdf\" target=\"_self\">AASHE</a>&nbsp;(pdf) and the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_innovation_webinar_sept_2012_elon_academy_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Elon University</a>&nbsp;(pdf).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/b1RLOR1-g7w?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/b1RLOR1-g7w?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><em><span class=\"regTextItem\"><a name=\"human_resources\" target=\"_self\"></a>Highlighting Best Practices from the Human Resources Sub-category</span></em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday August 21 at 2 p.m. Eastern.</p>\r\n<p>AASHE has learned that there are questions among the higher education community about how to approach the &ldquo;unusual suspects&rdquo; when working on sustainability projects and programs.&nbsp; One department on a college campus that sustainability offices may not work with very often is Human Resources.&nbsp; This webinar discussed communication strategies as well specific credits in the Human Resources subcategory of STARS - in particular PAE 11: Sustainable Compensation. This webinar also highlighted a best practice case study from a STARS Participant.</p>\r\n<p>The webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Trey McDonald, Sustainability Coordinator, University of North Carolina at Greensboro</li>\r\n<li>Dr. Edna Chun, Associate Vice Chancellor for Human Resources, University of North Carolina at Greensboro</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed presentation of the webinar content as presented by <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/aug_webinar_ppt.pdf\" target=\"_self\">AASHE</a> (pdf) and the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_aug_webinar_uncg.pdf\" target=\"_self\">University of North Carolina at Greensboro</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/4Rsqi-6gOzw?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/4Rsqi-6gOzw?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><em><span class=\"regTextItem\"><a name=\"energy\" target=\"_self\"></a>Highlighting Best Practices from the Energy Sub-category</span></em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, June 26 at 2:00 p.m. Eastern<a href=\"https://www2.gotomeeting.com/register/672332682\" target=\"_self\"></a>.</p>\r\n<p>AASHE has learned that there are questions among the higher education  community about how to approach specific credits in the Energy  subcategory of STARS.  In particular, OP 7: Building Energy Consumption.  This webinar highlighted a case study from a STARS Participant that  illustrated best practices for approaching this credit.</p>\r\n<p>The webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Steve Karcher, Vice President of Operations and Sustainability, Berea College</li>\r\n<li>\r\n<div class=\"O2\">Diane Zekind, Energy Manager, Berea College</div>\r\n</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/june_webinar_ppt.pptx\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of webinar content as presented by AASHE and <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/berea_college_june_2012_stars_webinar.ppt\" target=\"_self\">Berea College</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/EAeKBJJyckY?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/EAeKBJJyckY?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"brand\" target=\"_self\"></a>New and Improved AASHE Brand:  Where we were, where we&rsquo;re going, and what this means for STARS Institutions</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, May 29 at 2:00 p.m. Eastern.<a href=\"https://www2.gotomeeting.com/register/985414514\" target=\"_blank\"></a></p>\r\n<p>AASHE has been working on its branding and recently unveiled its new AASHE and STARS logos. We&rsquo;ve taken a very close look at how our organization functions,  the purpose it serves, and the best way to communicate who we are with  the higher education community and beyond.  This webinar shared the  details of the branding process, from concept to implementation, as well  as how the new brand affects STARS Institutions.</p>\r\n<p>This webinar featured the following presenter:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/may_webinar_ppt.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of the webinar content.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/SmW8NOEs3J4?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/SmW8NOEs3J4?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"curriculum_subcategory\" target=\"_self\"></a>Highlighting Best Practices from the Curriculum Subcategory</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, April 24th at 2:00 p.m. Eastern.<a href=\"https://www2.gotomeeting.com/register/666280698\" target=\"_self\"></a></p>\r\n<p>AASHE has learned that there are questions among the higher education community about how to approach specific credits in the Curriculum subcategory of STARS.&nbsp; In particular, ER 5: Sustainability Course Inventory, ER 6: Sustainability-Focused Courses, and ER 7: Sustainability-Related Courses. This webinar highlighted case studies from STARS Participants that illustrate best practices for approaching these credits.</p>\r\n<p>This webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Andrew Greene, Sustainability Planner, University of Virginia</li>\r\n<li>Carla Jones, Graduate Student, University of Virginia </li>\r\n<li>Linda Kosten, Assistant Provost, Planning, Budget, &amp; Analysis, University of Denver</li>\r\n<li>Federico (Fred) Cheever, Senior Associate Dean, Academic Affairs, Professor, Sturm College of Law, Chair, University Sustainability Council, University of Denver</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/april_2012_webinar__curriculum_subcategory_1.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of the webinar content by AASHE and the University of Virginia.&nbsp; Due to technical difficulties a video of this webinar is not available.</p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"finalizing\" target=\"_self\"></a>Finalizing a STARS Report in Record Time</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, Mar. 27, 2012 at 2 p.m. Eastern.<a href=\"https://www2.gotomeeting.com/register/654455002\" target=\"_self\"></a></p>\r\n<p>AASHE has learned that there are questions among the higher education community about the time commitment and number of resources required to complete a STARS Report. This webinar highlighted institutions that have completed their STARS Report in minimal time with maximum benefits. View the presentations and video from this webinar to learn the strategies these institutions have implemented to reduce the amount of time and dollars spent completing a STARS Report, while engaging the community and furthering sustainability on their campuses.</p>\r\n<p>This webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Gordie Bennett, Sustainability Manager, University of Tennessee at Knoxville</li>\r\n<li>Sarah Wald, Assistant Professor, Environmental Studies, Drew University</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/march_2012_webinar__completing_stars_record_time.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of the webinar content as well as a <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/drew_university_student_stars_presentation.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) created by Drew University students outlining their experience completing STARS through an academic course.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/QcONBHCpzkE?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/QcONBHCpzkE?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><em>STARS 1.2 and Enhancements to the STARS Reporting Tool</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Tuesday, Feb. 28, 2012 at 2 p.m. Eastern.<br /><br />With the release of STARS 1.2 and the Campus Sustainability Data Collector, there are new enhancements to the STARS Reporting Tool.&nbsp; This webinar gave an overview of the changes to the STARS Reporting Tool, highlighted its new functions, and explained how it is different from the Campus Sustainability Data Collector.&nbsp; Attendees learned new functionalities for documenting the institutional boundary, submitting Innovation Credits, and working in the newly added and optional supplemental section, where institutions are able to report additional data and share it with The Princeton Review, Sierra magazine and the Sustainable Endowments Institute.</p>\r\n<p>This webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Meghan Fay Zahniser, STARS Program Manager, AASHE</li>\r\n<li>Ben Stookey, STARS Web Developer, AASHE</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/february_2012_webinar__stars_1.2_and_reporting_tool_enhancements.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of the webinar content.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/wXOpS19I5kk?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/wXOpS19I5kk?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>\r\n<h2><em><a name=\"reducing_survey_fatigue\" target=\"_self\"></a>Reducing Survey Fatigue: A Collaboration with AASHE, Sustainable Endowments Institute, the Princeton Review, and Sierra magazine</em></h2>\r\n<p>This webinar was held on Wednesday, Feb. 1, 2012 at 2:00pm Eastern<a href=\"https://www2.gotomeeting.com/register/823611362\" target=\"_self\"></a></p>\r\n<p>Representatives from AASHE, the Sustainable Endowments Institute, the  Princeton Review, and Sierra magazine began meeting in March 2011 to  develop common campus sustainability survey language. The collaboration  then expanded to include designing a single survey web tool to eliminate  the need for institutions to complete four separate surveys. <br /> <br />This webinar discussed more about this effort and how it will reduce  survey fatigue for institutions participating in multiple frameworks  that evaluate campus sustainability. <br /> <br />This webinar featured the following presenters:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Jillian Buckholz, STARS Program Coordinator, AASHE </li>\r\n<li>Avital Binshtock, Sierra magazine </li>\r\n<li>Meghan Fay Zahniser, STARS Program Manager, AASHE </li>\r\n<li>Mark Orlowski, Sustainable Endowments Institute </li>\r\n<li>David Soto, the Princeton Review</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a detailed <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_webinar_ppt_2.1.11.pdf\" target=\"_self\">presentation</a> (pdf) of the webinar content.</p>\r\n<p>\r\n<object width=\"420\" height=\"315\">\r\n<param name=\"movie\" value=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/WplYnsa6UNI?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowFullScreen\" value=\"true\" />\r\n<param name=\"allowscriptaccess\" value=\"always\" /><embed src=\"http://www.youtube.com/v/WplYnsa6UNI?version=3&amp;hl=en_US\" type=\"application/x-shockwave-flash\" width=\"420\" height=\"315\" allowscriptaccess=\"always\" allowfullscreen=\"true\"></embed>\r\n</object>\r\n</p>',0,'2012-stars-webinars','',NULL,'2013-08-01 09:19:41'),
	(0,'My Resources','2010-02-15 08:49:43',29,'<h2>STARS Logo</h2>\r\n<p>Participants may wish to consult the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Brand_Guidelines.pdf\">STARS Brand Guidelines</a> (pdf) for guidance on using the Charter Participant logo.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Data Collection Tools</h2>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_1.0_Data_Tracking.xls\">STARS&nbsp;1.0 Data Tracking Spreadsheet</a> (xls) outlines the credits within each category and the reporting fields for each credit. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><em>Please note</em>: This optional resource is provided to help organize your institution\'s data collection process; all data will need to be saved in the online Reporting Tool in order to report officially. Participants are encouraged to use the Reporting Tool throughout the data collection process.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>To facilitate the data collection process, a <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%201.0%20Credits%20from%20Technical%20Manual.doc\">Word version of the STARS&nbsp;1.0 credits</a> (doc) is available for download. You may also download the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_1.0.1_Technical_Manual.pdf\">PDF version of the complete Technical Manual</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h2>STARS Update</h2>\r\n<p>The STARS Update is a free, monthly e-newsletter. Your subscription will keep you up to speed on the latest STARS news, resources, participant highlights, events, and more. <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/user/newsletters\">Subscribe Today! </a></p>\r\n<h2>Institutional Resources</h2>\r\n<p>The following resources have been provided by STARS&nbsp;participants to share with other registered institutions.&nbsp; To submit a resource to be posted here please contact <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<p>California State University, Channel Islands<br />\r\nProvided by <a href=\"mailto:laurel.replogle909@csuci.edu\">Laurel Replogle</a>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%20Operations%20Category%20Tracking%20Spreadsheet_CSU%20Channel%20Islands.accdb\">STARS&nbsp;Operations Category Tracking Spreadsheet</a> (accdb)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>San Diego State University<br />\r\nProvided by <a href=\"mailto:sd.campbell23@gmail.com\">Sarah Campbell</a> and <a href=\"mailto:mhudson@mail.sdsu.edu\">Mariah Hudson.</a></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/SDSU%20STARS%20Faculty%20Survey%20Questions.doc\">STARS&nbsp;Faculty Survey Questions</a> (doc)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>University of California, San Diego<br />\r\nProvided by <a href=\"mailto:msouder@ucsd.edu\">Maggie Souder</a>.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Contacts%20Tracking%20Spreadsheet_UCSD.xls\">STARS&nbsp;Contact Tracking Spreadsheet</a> (xls)</li>\r\n    <li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%20Education%20and%20Research%20spreadsheet%20for%20key%20stakeholder_UCSD.xls\">STARS Education &amp;&nbsp;Research Spreadsheet for Key Stakeholders</a> (xls)</li>\r\n    <li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS%20Operations%20spreadsheet%20for%20key%20stakeholder_UCSC.xls\">STARS&nbsp;Operations Spreadsheet for Key Stakeholders</a> (xls)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h2>Template Press Release</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/P_Template_Press_Release_8.26.10.doc\">Template press release announcing STARS participation</a> (doc)</p>\r\n<p>Charter Participants may modify and use this press release template to announce their participation in STARS.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Template Emails</h2>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Announcing%20STARS%20to%20Your%20Institution_email%20template.doc\">Announcing STARS&nbsp;to&nbsp;Your Institution Email Template</a> (doc)</p>\r\n<p>The intention of this email template is to announce your institution\'s participation in STARS&nbsp;to campus stakeholders and notify these individuals that they may be contacted for information regarding the STARS&nbsp;credits. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Colleague%20Outreach%20Email%20Template%206.30.10.doc\">Colleague Outreach Email Template</a> (doc)</p>\r\n<p>Participants may modify this email template to connect with colleagues at other institutions that are not yet participating in the STARS&nbsp;program.&nbsp; The Colleague Outreach Email Template details the benefits of the STARS program as well as the August 20, 2010 Charter Participant registration deadline.</p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Requesting%20Departmental%20Data%20for%20STARS_email%20template_0.doc\">Requesting Departmental Data for STARS&nbsp;Email&nbsp;Template</a> (doc)</p>\r\n<p>This email template was designed to assist STARS&nbsp;Liaisons in the data collection process and may be used to request information for specific STARS credits from campus stakeholders.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>STARS Overview Presentation</h2>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARSPPT_0.ppt\">STARS&nbsp;Overview Presentation</a> (ppt) highlights the details of the STARS&nbsp;program.&nbsp; Use this resource to share information about the STARS&nbsp;program with your institution.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>AASHE&nbsp;Campus Sustainability Resource Center</h2>\r\n<p>For more information and resources on sustainability efforts in higher education, please visit the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/resources\">AASHE Campus Sustainability Resource Center</a>.  The AASHE Campus Sustainability Resource Center is the home of many resources in the areas of publications, general sustainability, education &amp; research, operations, and planning, administration &amp; engagement.</p>\r\n<p>Please note some of the resources in the AASHE Campus Sustainability Resource Center are locked, and therefore only available to AASHE member institutions with a valid <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/accounts/help\">AASHE&nbsp;account</a>.  For more information on AASHE membership, please visit the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/membership/description.php\">AASHE membership</a> webpage.</p>',1,'my-resources','<h2>STARS Logo</h2>\r\n<p>Participants may wish to consult the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Brand_Guidelines.pdf\">STARS Brand Guidelines</a> (pdf) for guidance on using the Charter Participant logo.&nbsp;</p>',4554,'2010-12-08 21:01:50'),
	(600,'STARS Pilot Project','2010-02-18 14:57:04',30,'<p><a href=\"#STARS_Pilot_Project\" target=\"_self\">STARS&nbsp;Pilot Project</a><br /> <a href=\"#Institutions_Participating_in_the_STARS_Pilot\" target=\"_self\">Institutions Participating in the STARS Pilot</a><br /> <a href=\"#STARS_Pilot_Project_Conference_Calls_\" target=\"_self\">STARS Pilot Project Conference Calls</a></p>\r\n<h2><strong><a name=\"STARS_Pilot_Project\" target=\"_self\"></a></strong>Approach</h2>\r\n<p>The STARS pilot project took place from February 2008 to January 2009. Institutions that participated in the pilot tested the system and provided feedback to AASHE to help shape future versions of STARS.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The STARS pilot project took place in two phases. A phased approach helped to moderate the workload for participating institutions. It also allowed AASHE to solicit another round of feedback about some sections included in STARS before asking schools to gather data.</p>\r\n<p>Phase One of the STARS pilot started in February 2008. Phase One covers the Operations category and about half of the Administration and Finance category. View <span class=\"spaced_list\"><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/documents/stars/STARS_Pilot_Phase_One_Guide.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Guide to Pilot Phase One</a> (pdf)</span>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>STARS Pilot Phase Two started in September 2008.&nbsp; Phase Two covers the Education and Research category and remaining credits in the Administration and Finance category, as well as Tier Two Credits and Innovation Credits.&nbsp; View <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/documents/stars/STARS_Pilot_Phase_Two.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Guide to Pilot Phase Two</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h2>Results</h2>\r\n<p>The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/STARS_Pilot_Results.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Sustainability Tracking, Assessment &amp; Rating System Pilot Project Results</a> (pdf) is a detailed summary of results and feedback received during the pilot project.</p>\r\n<h2>Student Research</h2>\r\n<p>Kyle Murphy, a student at The Evergreen State College, coordinated his institution\'s participation in the STARS Pilot Project and wrote his Master\'s thesis about lessons learned from that experience.&nbsp; He writes:</p>\r\n<address>This research focused on three main questions with respect to Evergreen&rsquo;s use of the STARS tool: (a) Is STARS an effective tool for use at Evergreen (did the framework address issues important to Evergreen, did it meet the criteria of an ideal assessment framework, and what are the advantages and disadvantages), (b) Does the STARS process lead to organizational learning, and (c) What STARS reveal about Evergreen&rsquo;s commitment to sustainability. Using a case study research design, I took a multi-disciplinary approach to the data collection for STARS implementation. Through my research I found that STARS is an effective tool to evaluate sustainability at Evergreen, which led to organizational learning, and highlighted Evergreen&rsquo;s complex and dynamic commitment to sustainability.</address>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/Murphy_STARS_Evergreen.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Thesis presentation</a> (pdf)<br /> <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/resources/student-research/2009/Murphy_K MESThesis_2009.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Thesis full text</a> (pdf)</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong><a name=\"Institutions_Participating_in_the_STARS_Pilot\" target=\"_self\"></a>Institutions Participating in the STARS Pilot</strong></h1>\r\n<p>Institutions are listed below according to their basic Carnegie Classification and student population.</p>\r\n<h2><strong>Associate\'s Colleges</strong></h2>\r\n<p><strong>Large (more than 12,500 students)</strong><br /> Cedar Valley College &ndash; Lancaster, Texas<br /> De Anza Community College &ndash; Cupertino, California<br /> Eastfield College &ndash; Mesquite, Texas <br /> Grand Rapids Community College &ndash; Grand Rapids, Michigan<br /> Monroe Community College &ndash; Rochester, New York<br /> Mountain View College &ndash; Dallas, Texas <br /> North Lake College &ndash; Irving, Texas<br /> Richland College &ndash; Dallas, Texas<br /> Santa Barbara City College &ndash; Santa Barbara, California<br /> Santa Fe Community College &ndash; Santa Fe, New Mexico</p>\r\n<p><strong>Medium (3,000 to 12,500 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Delta College &ndash; University Center, Michigan<br /> Northwest State Community College &ndash; Archbold, Ohio</p>\r\n<p><strong>Districts</strong></p>\r\n<p>Dallas County Community College District &ndash; Dallas, Texas<br /> Eastern Iowa Community College District &ndash; Davenport, Iowa</p>\r\n<h2>Baccalaureate Colleges</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Small (fewer than 3,000 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>College of St. Benedict &ndash; St. Joseph, Minnesota<br /> Dickinson College &ndash; Carlisle, Pennsylvania<br /> Gustavus Adolphus College &ndash; St. Peter, Minnesota<br /> Middlebury College &ndash; Middlebury, Vermont<br /> Mount Union College &ndash; Alliance, Ohio<br /> Northland College &ndash; Ashland, Wisconsin<br /> Randolph College &ndash; Lynchburg, Virginia<br /> St. John\'s University &ndash; Collegeville, Minnesota<br /> University of Minnesota, Morris &ndash; Morris, Minnesota<br /> Williams College &ndash; Williamstown, Massachusetts</p>\r\n<h2>Canadian Institutions</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Large (more than 12,500 students)</strong><br /> Concordia University &ndash; Montreal, Quebec<br /> McGill University &ndash; Montreal, Quebec<br /> University of British Columbia &ndash; Vancouver, British Columbia</p>\r\n<p><strong>Medium (3,000 to 12,000 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Acadia University - Wolfville, Nova Scotia</p>\r\n<h2>Doctorate-granting Universities</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Large (more than 12,500 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Arizona State University &ndash; Tempe, Arizona<br /> Ball State University &ndash; Muncie, Indiana<br /> Colorado State University &ndash; Fort Collins, Colorado<br /> Illinois State University &ndash; Normal, Illinois<br /> Iowa State University &ndash; Ames, Iowa<br /> New York University &ndash;New York, New York<br /> Portland State University &ndash; Portland, Oregon<br /> Rutgers, The State University of New Jersey &ndash; New Brunswick, New Jersey<br /> Syracuse University &ndash; Syracuse, New York<br /> University of California, San Diego &ndash; San Diego, California<br /> University of California, Santa Barbara &ndash; Santa Barbara, California<br /> University of Central Florida &ndash; Orlando, Florida<br /> University of Colorado at Boulder &ndash; Boulder, Colorado<br /> University of Florida &ndash; Gainesville, Florida<br /> University of Illinois at Chicago &ndash; Chicago, Illinois<br /> University of Kansas &ndash; Lawrence, Kansas<br /> University of New Hampshire &ndash; Durham, New Hampshire<br /> University of Texas at Austin &ndash; Austin, Texas<br /> Worcester Polytechnic Institute &ndash; Worcester, Massachusetts</p>\r\n<p><strong>Medium (3,000 to 12,000 students)</strong><br /> Case Western Reserve University &ndash; Cleveland, Ohio<br /> Emory University &ndash; Atlanta, Georgia</p>\r\n<p><strong>Small (fewer than 3,000 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>State University of New York, College of Environmental Science &amp; Forestry &ndash; Syracuse, NY</p>\r\n<h2>Master\'s Colleges and Universities</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Large (more than 12,500 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Appalachian State University &ndash; Boone, North Carolina<br /> Boise State University &ndash; Boise, Idaho<br /> California State University, Chico &ndash; Chico, California<br /> California State University, Sacramento &ndash; Sacramento, California<br /> Eastern Kentucky University &ndash; Richmond, Kentucky<br /> Grand Valley State University &ndash; Allendale, Michigan<br /> University of Nebraska at Omaha &ndash; Omaha, Nebraska</p>\r\n<p><strong>Medium (3,000 to 12,000 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Florida Gulf Coast University &ndash; Fort Meyers, Florida<br /> Pacific Lutheran University &ndash; Tacoma, Washington<br /> Santa Clara University &ndash; Santa Clara, California<br /> Seattle Pacific University &ndash; Seattle, Washington<br /> The Evergreen State College &ndash; Olympia, Washington<br /> University of Colorado at Colorado Springs &ndash; Colorado Springs, Colorado<br /> University of Wisconsin - River Falls &ndash; River Falls, Wisconsin</p>\r\n<p><strong>Small (fewer than 3,000 students)</strong><br /> Monterey Institute of International Studies &ndash; Monterey, California</p>\r\n<h2>Special Focus Institutions</h2>\r\n<p><strong>Small (fewer than 3,000 students)</strong></p>\r\n<p>Rose-Hulman Institute of Technology &ndash; Terre Haute, Indiana</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h1><strong><a name=\"STARS_Pilot_Project_Conference_Calls_\" target=\"_self\"></a>STARS Pilot Project Conference Calls </strong></h1>\r\n<p>Throughout the pilot period, AASHE conducted a series of conference calls focused on the categories covered by STARS. The calls provided an opportunity for institutions participating in the pilot project to ask questions, provide feedback, and share strategies for gathering data and achieving the credits. Calls were open only to institutions participating in the STARS pilot project.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Pilot Phase Two Calls</h2>\r\n<p><strong>1. Co-Curricular Education and Faculty and Staff Development and Training Call</strong><br /> Thursday, September 18th, 2008, 11:00 a.m. &ndash; 12:00 p.m. <em>Pacific Daylight Time</em><br /> <em><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/stars/pilot/CoCurric_FacStaffDev_Call_Notes.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Summary notes</a> </em>(pdf)  <br /> <br /> <strong>2. Curriculum Call </strong><br /> Thursday, September 25th, 2008, 11:00 a.m. &ndash; 12:00 p.m.<em> Pacific Daylight Time<br /> <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/stars/pilot/Curriculum_Call_Notes.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Summary notes</a> </em>(pdf) <br /> <br /> <strong>3. Resea