	(400,'Benefits','2013-07-30 12:43:09',95,'<p>Once an institution registers for STARS, and the registration fee has been submitted to AASHE, the institution is recognized as a STARS Participant.&nbsp; STARS Participants receive 12-months of continuous access to the STARS Reporting Tool and are encouraged to submit their inaugural STARS Report during this time frame. Once a STARS Participant submits its STARS Report and earns a STARS rating, this rating is valid for three years.&nbsp; However, STARS Participants are encouraged to participate in STARS on an annual basis and have the opportunity to do so, at a discounted rate, so they can continue tracking their STARS data.</p>\r\n<table border=\"1\" cellspacing=\"3\" cellpadding=\"10\" align=\"center\">\r\n<tbody>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td><strong>STARS Fees</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>First-time Participants</strong></td>\r\n<td><strong>Annual Participants</strong></td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>AASHE Member</td>\r\n<td>$900</td>\r\n<td>$450</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n<tr>\r\n<td>Non-member</td>\r\n<td>$1,400</td>\r\n<td>$700</td>\r\n</tr>\r\n</tbody>\r\n</table>\r\n<h2>Benefits</h2>\r\n<p>Benefits of becoming a STARS Participant include, but are not limited to:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Access to the online <strong>STARS Reporting Tool</strong>, which includes:</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -<strong> Data synchronization</strong> with other specific rating and ranking organizations<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - <strong>Automated point calculation</strong> for each STARS credit<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -<strong> PDF Exports</strong> of Submission Data<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Ability to <strong>share data </strong>with other organizations outside of AASHE<br /> &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - <strong>Continuous access </strong>to update data<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Option to give <strong>multiple users access</strong> to the STARS Report<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -<strong> Data tracking resources</strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; -<strong> STARS seal</strong> <strong>logo</strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <strong>- Email templates</strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - Template <strong>press release</strong><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; - <strong>Promotional tools</strong></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Earn a STARS rating and <strong>be recognized as a STARS rated institution</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Publicly posted STARS Report</strong> on the STARS website</li>\r\n<li>Full access to&nbsp;<strong>STARS Data Displays</strong></li>\r\n<li>Opportunities to <strong>influence STARS technical development</strong></li>\r\n<li>Inclusion in <strong>STARS Quarterly Review</strong></li>\r\n<li><strong>Free admission</strong> to STARS webinars</li>\r\n<li>And more!</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>View a printable version of the STARS Participant <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/benefits_of_participating_in_stars_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">benefits</a> (pdf).</p>',0,'benefits','',NULL,'2013-07-31 08:48:11'),
	(100,'Getting Started','2013-07-30 12:48:09',96,'<p><span> </span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Whether you&rsquo;re new to STARS or a returning Participant, AASHE recommends taking a few steps before you dive into data documentation:</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span>Download the&nbsp;</span><a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/report/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Manual</a><span>&nbsp;and review the STARS credits</span></li>\r\n<li><span>Determine an approach to data collection (see below)</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Identify your data collection team&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Familiarize yourself with the </span><a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/report/reporting-process.html\" target=\"_self\">Reporting Process</a></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Review the requirements of the <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/submit/submission-process.html\" target=\"_self\">Submission Process</a></span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<p>STARS Participants may access additional resources including data collection tools, STARS seals, and template press releases, in the \'My Resources\' section of the STARS Reporting Tool.</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Get Organized, Collect Data </span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>[Have photos or testimonials from campuses]</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">There are several different approaches to collecting STARS data. &nbsp;Which option is best for your campus? &nbsp;If your data collection team is outside of these examples, please let us know at <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>The sustainability champion</strong> - a single energetic individual that leads the organization of STARS on their campus, including: data collection, documentation, submission, and post-submission marketing and communication.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>A sustainability office or committee</strong> - a group of diverse campus stakeholders that divide the data collection by the categories and subcategories of the STARS Technical Manual.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>STARS courses</strong> - usually lead by an enthusiastic faculty person, courses may be created to focuses solely on STARS or STARS may be integrated into an existing course. &nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Individual student projects</strong> - this option has taken different forms, such as a graduate student thesis project or the focus of a student intern for course credit.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<h3>Resources</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/screen_shot_2012-05-23_at_9.00.34_am.png\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" align=\"left\" />The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_brochure_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Brochure</a> (pdf) and <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_flyer_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Flyer</a> (pdf) are documents created by AASHE with the intention of sharing a brief snapshot of STARS including benefits and how the program works.&nbsp; Both resources may be shared with your colleagues, community members, and campus to communicate information about STARS.</p>\r\n<p>The STARS Flyer is a one-page document while the STARS Brochure is a two-page document where each page is intended to be printed back-to-back on a single sheet of paper and folded.&nbsp; Please see the STARS Brochure <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/flyer_brochure_instructions_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">printing instructions</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/screen_shot_2012-05-23_at_9.01.41_am.png\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p>The STARS&nbsp;Overview     Presentation (<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview_presentation.pptx\" target=\"_self\">ppt</a> | <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview_presentation.pdf\" target=\"_self\">pdf</a>)  highlights the details of STARS.&nbsp;   Use this resource to  share information about STARS with  your  institution.</p>',1,'getting-started','',NULL,'2013-09-13 11:58:35'),
	(200,'Resources','2013-07-30 12:49:09',97,'<p>STARS Participants may access additional resources, such as data collection tools, STARS seals, and template press releases, in the \'My Resources\' section of the STARS Reporting Tool.</p>\r\n<h3>STARS Brochure &amp; Flyer</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/screen_shot_2012-05-23_at_9.00.34_am.png\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" align=\"left\" />The&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_brochure_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Brochure</a> (pdf) and <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_flyer_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Flyer</a> (pdf) are documents created by AASHE with the intention of sharing a brief snapshot of the STARS Program including benefits and how the program works.&nbsp; Both resources may be shared with your colleagues, community members, and campus to communicate information about the STARS Program.</p>\r\n<p>The STARS Flyer is a one-page document while the STARS Brochure is a two-page document where each page is intended to be printed back-to-back on a single sheet of paper and folded.&nbsp; Please see the STARS Brochure <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/flyer_brochure_instructions_final.pdf\" target=\"_self\">printing instructions</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>STARS Overview Presentation&nbsp;</h3>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/screen_shot_2012-05-23_at_9.01.41_am.png\" border=\"0\" hspace=\"10\" width=\"225\" height=\"169\" align=\"left\" /></p>\r\n<p>The STARS&nbsp;Overview     Presentation (<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview_presentation.pptx\" target=\"_self\">ppt</a> | <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview_presentation.pdf\" target=\"_self\">pdf</a>)  highlights the details of the  STARS&nbsp;program.&nbsp;   Use this resource to  share information about the STARS&nbsp;program with  your  institution.</p>',0,'resources','',NULL,'2013-08-22 13:54:43'),
	(300,'Governance','2013-07-30 12:49:59',98,'<p><span> </span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_governance_structure.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS governance structure</a>&nbsp;(pdf) includes the <a href=\"#steering_committee\" target=\"_self\">STARS Steering Committee</a>, <a href=\"#technical_advisors\" target=\"_self\">Technical Advisors</a>, <a href=\"/pages/stars-partner-organizations.html\" target=\"_self\">Partner Organizations</a>, and <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/about/governance/board\" target=\"_self\">AASHE&rsquo;s Board of Directors</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><span>Goals</span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The goals of the STARS governance structure are to:</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Engage the higher education community in providing technical and strategic guidance for STARS</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Facilitate continuous improvement of STARS</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\">\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Provide strategic guidance to STARS, including sound financial oversight</span></p>\r\n</li>\r\n<li dir=\"ltr\"><span>Enhance the transparency of STARS&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Participation</h3>\r\n<p><span> </span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>STARS is a highly collaborative project. AASHE offers several opportunities for &nbsp;stakeholder engagement:</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Governance Bodies</strong><br /> AASHE periodically solicits applications for STARS Steering Committee members, STARS Technical Advisors, and AASHE Board members. Organizations may email <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a> to inquire about becoming a STARS Partner Organization at any time.<span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Public Comment Periods</strong><br /> Major revisions to STARS (e.g. 2.0, 3.0) occur no more often than once every three years according to the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/technical_development_policy.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Development Policy</a> and are vetted through an extensive process of deliberation and public comment.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Stay tuned to the </span><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/connect/enewsletters\" target=\"_self\"><span>AASHE Bulletin</span></a><span> and social media for calls for applications and public comment periods.</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Continuous Feedback</strong><br /> In addition to the above, feedback on STARS is welcome at all times. Community feedback helps drive the improvement of STARS. Please send suggestions and comments to <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<p><span> </span></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\"><span><a name=\"steering_committee\" target=\"_self\"></a>Steering Committee Members</span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>The STARS Steering Committee is comprised of campus representatives, members of the AASHE Board of Directors, and AASHE Staff. STARS Steering Committee members advise on program policy, finances, and strategic positioning, in addition to reviewing and approving updates and revisions to the technical content of STARS, including each new version. &nbsp;</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>Campus Representatives</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Julian Dautremont-Smith</span><span> - Chief Sustainability Officer, Alfred State College</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Jeremy Friedman -</span><span>Manager, Sustainability Initiatives, New York University</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Elaine Hanson</span><span> - Director, Office for Sustainability, Sheridan College</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Preston Jacobsen</span><span> - Sustainability Analyst, Haywood Community College</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Nurit Katz - </span><span>Chief Sustainability Officer, University of California, Los Angeles</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>H. Scott Matthews </span><span>- Faculty and Research Director, Carnegie Mellon University</span><span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Chris O\'Brien</span><span> - Director of Sustainability, American University</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Stephenie Presseller</span><span> - Sustainability Manager, Moraine Valley Community College</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Cindy Shea</span><span> - Director, Sustainability Office, University of North Carolina at Chapel Hill</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>AASHE Board Members </strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">William Brown <span>- Director of Sustainability, &nbsp;Indiana University</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Jon Jensen<span> - Director of Environmental Studies, Luther College</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Dave Newport<span> - Director, Environmental Center, University of Colorado at Boulder</span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><strong>AASHE Staff</strong></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Meghan Fay Zahniser<span> - Director of Programs, AASHE</span></p>\r\n<p>For additional information about each individual Steering Committee member, please view the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/2013_sc_bios_pics.pdf\" target=\"_self\"><span>Steering Committee Members\' bios</span></a> (pdf). <span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Learn more about Steering Committee discussions by viewing </span><a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/engage/steering-committee-minutes.html\" target=\"_self\">meeting minutes from this year</a><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> or </span><a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/engage/archived-stars-steering-committee-minutes.html\" target=\"_self\">archived Steering Committee meeting minutes</a><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">.</span></p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"technical_advisors\" target=\"_self\"></a>Technical Advisors</h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">STARS Technical Advisors are the primary source for input and insight regarding the content of STARS credits. Technical Advisors are drawn from higher education institutions, non-profit organizations, and businesses, with preference given for AASHE members. Individuals nominated by STARS Partner Organizations&nbsp;are given special consideration during the selection process.</span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Meet the current <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_tas.pdf\" target=\"_self\">Technical Advisors</a> (pdf).</p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"partner_organizations\" target=\"_self\"></a>Partner Organizations</h3>\r\n<p>STARS Partner Organizations are higher education associations and other non-profit organizations that provide value to the development and promotion of STARS. These organizations work to educate their constituents about STARS and engage them in its ongoing refinement and development.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Partner Organizations enjoy the following benefits:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>At opportunity to nominate a member, constituent, or staff person to serve as a Technical Advisor to STARS</li>\r\n<li>Recognition on the STARS website and in the STARS Technical Manual</li>\r\n<li>Access to materials to help educate their members and constituents about STARS</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Please email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>&nbsp;to inquire about becoming a STARS&nbsp;Partner Organization.</p>\r\n<p><em>For additional details about the STARS governance structure, including roles, responsibilities, selection criteria and terms of engagement, see the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_governance_structure.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Governance Structure</a>&nbsp;(pdf) document.&nbsp;View a list of&nbsp;<a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/engage/previous-committee-members.html#\" target=\"_self\">previous committee members</a>&nbsp;that contributed to the development of STARS.</em></p>',1,'governance','',NULL,'2013-08-28 10:46:12'),
