	(0,'Reporting Process','2013-07-30 12:55:36',100,'<p><span> </span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Getting started in the STARS Reporting Tool is simple. &nbsp;Any individual that is listed as a \'user\' in the STARS Reporting Tool has access and may log-in with an&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/user/register\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Account</a>. Not&nbsp;listed as a \'user\'? Contact your institution\'s STARS Liaison or send an email to <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Once you\'ve logged into the STARS Reporting Tool, start by completing the Institutional Characteristics section. &nbsp;Then, determine if a version migration or data migration makes sense for your institution. &nbsp;Next, document data in the appropriate fields for each STARS credit. &nbsp;After a final review you\'ll be ready to learn more about the <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/submit/submission-process.html\" target=\"_self\">submission process</a>.</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Institutional Characteristics<span style=\"font-size: 1.4em; line-height: 1.2;\">&nbsp;</span></h3>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>This section requests three types of data. For example:</span><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<ol>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Defining an institution&rsquo;s boundary for reporting purposes</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> &ndash; If an institution owns a hospital, are its operational and academic attributes included in STARS?</span></li>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Operational characteristics</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> &ndash; How much of an institution&rsquo;s gross floor area is laboratory space?</span></li>\r\n<li><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Demographics and academics</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> &ndash; What proportion of student FTE enrollment is residential full-time students?</span></li>\r\n</ol> <ol> </ol>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span> </span></p>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\"><span>Consolidation of institutional characteristics data into a single section within STARS provides the following benefits:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Institutions using STARS can review data in this section to facilitate the identification of peer institutions for </span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">benchmarking</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> purposes (data from this section may be used to create a new STARS benchmarking tool on the website).</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Placing operational characteristics and demographics into a single section will promote </span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">data accuracy</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> (Errors in these areas represent the majority of STARS data accuracy issues). Institutions can verify their own data in one location, and potential errors can be spotted more easily by third parties.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Several values in the Institutional Characteristics section are required to pursue one or more STARS credits. With the launch of STARS 2.0, the STARS Reporting Tool will feature an auto-population option that will </span><strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">streamline reporting</span></strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> by bringing these values into other areas of the report when relevant.</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Data Migration</h3>\r\n<p><strong>[SCREEN SHOTS OF PROCESS WHEN 2.0 IS IN RT]</strong></p>\r\n<p>Registered under a certain version of STARS when a new version is launched and want to switch version? Interested in working from a perviously saved dataset instead of documenting data in the Reporting Tool from scratch?&nbsp;<span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">No problem. &nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">\'Version Migrations\'&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">allow you to migrate between different versions of the STARS Technical Manual.&nbsp;</span><strong style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">\'Data Migration\'&nbsp;</strong><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">allows you to migrate previously saved data sets.&nbsp;For detailed information, visit the migrate function in the \'My Summary\' section of the STARS Reporting Tool.</span><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3>Documenting Data</h3>\r\n<p><strong>[SCREEN SHOT OF PROCESS <strong>WHEN 2.0 IS IN RT</strong>]</strong></p>\r\n<p>Each credit in the STARS Reporting Tool will ask for information in the following sections:</p>\r\n<p><strong>Reporting Fields</strong><br /> Reporting Fields in the STARS Reporting Tool are the spaces where you will submit data for the information requested in the \'Reporting Fields\' section of the STARS Technical Manual. &nbsp;Fields with a red asterisk are required, while those with a blue asterisk are conditionally required.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><strong>Notes</strong><br /> Any supplemental information that you\'d like to share publicly in your institution\'s STARS Report that is related to the credit, but doesn\'t fit in the Reporting Fields, may be documented in the \'Notes\' section. &nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>An \'Internal Notes\' tab is available in each credit in the STARS Reporting Tool as well. &nbsp;This section may be used to share notes in the Reporting Tool that are not shared publicly outside of the Reporting Tool.</p>\r\n<p><strong style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Responsible Party</strong></p>\r\n<p>As a <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/report/stars-report-accuracy.html\" target=\"_self\">data accuracy</a> measure, AASHE asks that a single Responsible Party is documented for each STARS credit. &nbsp;The individual should be the most appropriate person to direct questions regarding the data document in the credit, not the individual entering data into the STARS Reporting Tool for the specific credit.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Submission Status</strong><br /> These statuses are provided to help you manage the STARS submission process. You may return to any credit and update its status until the final submission is completed.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">\'Pursuing\' requires that all of the required fields have been&nbsp;completed.&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">\'In Progress\' indicates that you are still editing a credit. Please note that this status refers to an individual being \'In Progress\' of documenting information for the credit; not that the project or program the credit is asking about is \'In Progress.\'&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">\'Not Pursuing\' indicates that you do not wish to submit data for a&nbsp;credit. When the final submission is made public, only the \'Notes\' field for credits with this status will be made public. Institutions will&nbsp;not earn points for credits marked as \'Not Pursuing.\'&nbsp;</span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>If you would only like the notes section of the credit to be visible to the public, you may choose \'Not Pursuing\' for the credit.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h3>Continuous Access &amp; Sharing Data</h3>\r\n<p>All institutions that subscribe to STARS will have continuous access to update data in the STARS Reporting Tool. &nbsp;Those STARS Participants that wish to share data with organizations such as Sierra magazine and The Princeton Review may do so by following the instructions in the \'Share Data\' tab in the \'My Summary\' section of the STARS Reporting Tool.</p>',1,'reporting-process','',NULL,'2013-09-09 12:03:01'),
