	(100,'Participants & Reports','2013-07-30 13:06:56',103,'<p><span>Combine \"Current Participants\" and \"Rated Institutions\" on existing STARS website into a single \"Participants and Reports.\" &nbsp;All subscribed institutions are listed and those that have submitted a STARS Report are linked. &nbsp;Should be able to sort the list (which will be large) by version, submission date, and level of recognition.</span></p>',1,'participants-reports','',NULL,'2013-08-21 10:00:21'),
	(0,'Share Your Story','2013-07-30 13:07:30',104,'<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">Congratulations! &nbsp;You\'ve navigated through STARS, collected data, documented it, and submitted a completed STARS Report. What&rsquo;s next?</span></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Take Action</h3>\r\n<p>AASHE encourages all STARS participants to learn from their STARS Reports.&nbsp;Utilize the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/evaluate/data-displays.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Data Displays</a>&nbsp;to benchmark with peers and thoroughly review your institution\'s STARS Report to learn which sustainability efforts on your campus are successful, as well as identify areas of improvement.&nbsp;Your comprehensive STARS Report is a great guide to help organize future sustainability programming and prioritize efforts that will have the largest impact.<span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Showcase Your Efforts</h3>\r\n<p><span>Here are a just a few examples of the many efforts you can take to highlight your achievement and gain recognition.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"> </span></p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Show off your newly earned STARS seal</strong> - Navigate to the &lsquo;My Resources&rsquo; section of the STARS Reporting Tool to download the STARS seal and brand guidelines. &nbsp;Share your campus&rsquo; achievement by posting the STARS seal to your campus website, sustainability website, relevant newsletters, email signatures, and other visible locations.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Share STARS with campus stakeholders</strong> - Contact all of the individuals that helped you complete STARS, thank them for their efforts, share the link to your institution&rsquo;s STARS Report, and work together on ways to enhance sustainability initiatives in their area of campus.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Create a communication plan</strong> &nbsp;- Connect with your campus&rsquo; marketing and communications offices and design a strategy to gain recognition for your achievement with the campus and surrounding community. &nbsp;A template press release is available for your use in the &lsquo;My Resources&rsquo; section of the STARS Reporting Tool.</span></li>\r\n<li><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\"><strong>Use STARS as a recruitment tool</strong> - Highlight your achievement when connecting with potential new students and their parents to illustrate your campus&rsquo; commitment to sustainability.</span><em style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5;\">&nbsp;</em></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p><span><strong>[SCREEN SHOT OF INSTITUTIONAL RECOGNITION IN THE MEDIA - BC newsletter highlighting 3rd report?]</strong></span></p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">Shape the System</h3>\r\n<p>Throughout the STARS process AASHE encourages <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">feedback</a> from its participants. &nbsp;Now that your institution\'s STARS Report is complete, we encourage you more than ever to share questions and feedback to help shape the system. &nbsp;We take your comments very seriously - every phone call and email is documented and <span><span>and every suggestion for improvement is considered in developing future versions of STARS.</span></span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Interested in being more involved in the development of STARS? &nbsp;Familiarize yourself with our <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/engage/governance.html\" target=\"_self\">Governance</a> structure and stay tuned to the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/connect/enewsletters\" target=\"_self\">AASHE Bulletin</a> for calls for STARS Technical Advisors and Steering Committee members.</p>\r\n<h3 dir=\"ltr\">What People are Saying</h3>\r\n<p><span>[QUOTES FROM KUDOS FILE, NEED PERMISSION TO USE?]</span></p>\r\n<p><span><em>Has your institution been recognized in campus, local, or national media due to it&rsquo;s participation in STARS? &nbsp;If so, let us know and we&rsquo;ll highlight the article on our&nbsp;<a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/celebrate/media-coverage.html\" target=\"_self\">Media Coverage</a>&nbsp;page.</em><br /></span></p>',1,'share-your-story','',NULL,'2013-09-09 12:48:18'),
	(400,'Access STARS Data','2013-07-30 13:08:49',105,'<p>Should include the front page (including the average scores data visualization) of the Data Dashboard on the current site and the tabs for the Data Displays. &nbsp;</p>',1,'access-stars-data','',NULL,'2013-08-21 10:04:21'),
