ank\">AU: Member of Nation&rsquo;s 1st Campus Sustainability Program </a><br /> <a href=\"http://php.louisville.edu/advancement/ocm/news/release.php?relid=1316\" target=\"_blank\">UofL joins sustainability rating system</a><br /> <a href=\"https://louisville.edu/uofltoday/campus-news/university-joins-sustainability-rating-system\" target=\"_blank\">University joins sustainability rating system </a><br /> <a href=\"http://www.iowapolitics.com/index.iml?Article=182576\" target=\"_blank\">UNI: Charter participant in nation\'s first campus-wide sustainability program</a></p>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://asumag.com/dailynews/aashe-stars-assessment-green-sustainable-college-campus-20100120/\" target=\"_blank\">New system will help track campus sustainability</a></p>\r\n<h4>March 2008</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.ia.ucsb.edu/pa/display.aspx?pkey=1737\" target=\"_blank\">UCSB Will Help Set Standards for Sustainability on College Campuses</a></p>\r\n<h4>February 2008</h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://www.lipscomb.edu/filter.asp?SID=4&amp;fi_key=704&amp;co_key=13085\" target=\"_blank\">Lipscomb is first in state to test a new sustainability rating for its operations</a><br /> <a href=\"http://www.wcu.edu/6295.asp\" target=\"_blank\">WCU selected to test sustainability rating system</a><br /> <a href=\"http://www.gvsu.edu/gvnow/index.cfm?fuseaction=home.read_news&amp;id=FA285395-AD6F-FB29-D9F24E71961513AD\" target=\"_blank\">GVSU in pilot sustainability rating project</a><br /> <a href=\"http://news.csuchico.edu/2008/02/06/csu-chico-to-help-pilot-sustainability-rating-system-for-higher-education/\" target=\"_blank\">CSU, Chico to help pilot sustainability rating system for higher education</a><br /> <a href=\"http://www2.muc.edu/Newsroom/February08/stars_sustainability_rating_system_piloted_by_mount_union_college.aspx\" target=\"_blank\">Mount Union College pilots campus sustainability rating system</a><br /> <a href=\"http://www.esf.edu/communications/news/2008/02.05.stars.htm\" target=\"_blank\">SUNY-ESF joins campuses nationwide to pilot sustainability rating system for higher education</a><br /> <a href=\"http://www.csbsju.edu/news/2008/02/sustainability_rating.htm\" target=\"_blank\">CSB and SJU join pilot project for sustainability rating system for higher education</a></p>\r\n<h3><a name=\"other\" target=\"_self\"></a>Other</h3>\r\n<h4>2010<strong><a href=\"http://sustainabilityprofessionals.org/special-reports\" target=\"_blank\"></a></strong></h4>\r\n<p><a href=\"http://sustainabilityprofessionals.org/special-reports\" target=\"_blank\">Directory of Sustainability Assessments</a><br /> <a href=\"http://www.mossadams.com/publications/documents/international/Intl_zine_SpecialReport_Fall2010.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">Does Higher Ed Have Something to Teach the Private Sector?</a><strong><br /> </strong><a href=\"http://www.greenbuildconsult.com/pdfs/benchmarking.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">CAMPUS SUSTAINABILITY Peer Selection and Benchmarking</a><br /> <em></em></p>',1,'media-archive','<p>This archive contains national press, articles in campus newspapers and on campus websites, blog posts, press releases,  and other media coverage of STARS that has occurred more than a year  ago. For a complete list of more  up-to-date articles, please visit our <a href=\"../../../../pages/news-events/media-coverage.html\" target=\"_self\">Media Coverage</a> page.</p>',NULL,'2013-08-01 09:35:56'),
	(200,'2011 Publications','2012-03-07 15:14:48',82,'<p>The Association for the Advanc<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/stars_annual_review_2010.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS: A Year in Review\"><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/stars_annual_report_cover.jpg\" border=\"0\" alt=\"2010 STARS Annual Report Cover\" width=\"302\" height=\"351\" align=\"left\" /></a>ement  of Sustainability in Higher Education (AASHE) released its first annual  \"<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/stars_annual_review_2010.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS: A Year in Review\">STARS: A Year in Review</a>\" on April 14, 2011. This report details the sustainability efforts found in the inaugural submissions to the Sustainability Tracking, Assessment, Rating &amp; System (STARS), such as sustainability research opportunities, sustainable dining efforts, and campus-wide social justice initiatives.</p>\r\n<p>Thirty-seven <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/institutions/\" target=\"_self\">institutions </a>submitted their STARS Reports in time for  inclusion in the review. There are more than 200 additional institutions  participating in STARS that will be submitting reports for a rating in  the coming year.</p>\r\n<p>&ldquo;The STARS annual review provides a wealth of information about the  state of campus sustainability,&rdquo; said AASHE Executive Director Paul  Rowland. &ldquo;Case studies, best practices, exemplary programs, and  interesting facts can all be found in the document. We hope that it will  inspire continued growth of sustainability efforts in higher  education.&rdquo;</p>\r\n<p>In addition to a broad range of information provided in the  institutional reports submitted by STARS Participants, &ldquo;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/stars_annual_review_2010.pdf\" target=\"_self\" title=\"STARS: A Year in Review\">STARS: A Year in  Review</a>&rdquo; captures the insights and knowledge gained by those  institutions during the reporting process. Of particular note are the  following findings:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Of the first 37 submissions, which came from a variety of  institution types, eight earned a Gold Rating, 19 earned Silver, nine  earned Bronze, and one earned a Reporter Rating.</li>\r\n<li>Seven of the eight STARS Gold institutions scored more than 17 of  the 18 possible points in the Co-Curricular Education subcategory, which  focuses on non-academic programming that supports sustainability  learning.</li>\r\n<li>On average, 58% of the applicable points in the water subcategory were earned by STARS Participants.</li>\r\n<li>Ten institutions earned 100% of the points available in both the  Diversity and Affordability subcategory and the Coordination and  Planning subcategory, which together include a total of 13  sustainability indicators.</li>\r\n<li>A total of 71 sustainability innovations were reported (nearly two per institution)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>The STARS Program provides ongoing opportunities for institutions to   participate.&nbsp; Institutions that are ready to <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/registration.html\" target=\"_self\">register</a> may do so  online.&nbsp; More information about the STARS program can be obtained by  browsing the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/\" target=\"_self\">website</a>, reviewing the <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_overview.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Overview presentation</a> (pdf) or  contacting us at <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>',0,'2011-publications','',NULL,'2013-08-01 09:33:16'),
	(300,'Using STARS Data','2012-08-24 09:00:39',86,'<p>AASHE believes that transparency is a key component in communicating sustainability claims.&nbsp; As a result, STARS data are made publicly available in a number of ways.&nbsp; This information can be used outside of AASHE in research, benchmarking, and other publications, provided that certain guidelines are met (see <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/data_use_guidelines.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Data Use Guidelines</a>).</p>\r\n<h3>Sources of Data</h3>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>Individual <strong>STARS Reports</strong> can be publicly accessed from the <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/celebrate/rated-institutions.html\" target=\"_self\">Rated Institutions</a> page of the STARS website.</li>\r\n<li>STARS <strong>Data Displays</strong> provide an overview of STARS data updated daily.&nbsp; For descriptions, links, and helpful tips related to the data displays, <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/data_display_tips.pdf\" target=\"_self\">click here</a>.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>The <strong>STARS API</strong> is a new tool from AASHE that enables different software programs to better respond to requests to share STARS data. The first release of the API provides a software-based interface to the STARS Technical Manual and STARS Reports, opening the door for interesting analysis and collaboration. &nbsp;The STARS <a href=\"http://stars-api-documentation.readthedocs.org/en/latest/index.html\" target=\"_self\">API Documentation</a> page provides more information on this exciting new tool.&nbsp;</li>\r\n<li>Website users can access the <strong>STARS Quarterly Review </strong>to learn about the current research on STARS data conducted by AASHE.&nbsp; Found on the <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/celebrate/publications.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Publications</a> page, the Reviews also include best practices on a number of sustainability topics. <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/archive/previous-publications.html\" target=\"_self\">View archived publications</a>.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<h3>Accessibility of STARS Data</h3>\r\n<p>Although AASHE provides a number of options for accessing STARS data, current AASHE Members and STARS Participants enjoy enhanced access to certain <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/evaluate/data-displays.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Data Displays</a>.&nbsp; While enhanced access to STARS data represents added value for Members and Participants, AASHE wishes to encourage research that advances sustainability across the spectrum.&nbsp; For this reason, individuals conducting sustainability research who do not currently have access to STARS Data Displays can request temporary access at&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>For any other questions about using or accessing STARS data that are not covered in this section of the website, please contact <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<h3>Data Accuracy<span style=\"white-space: pre;\"> </span></h3>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12px; line-height: 1.5; white-space: pre;\">STARS data accuracy processes help to protect the credibility of STARS and provide a fair and transparent means for resolving questions about the accuracy of STARS data. View the <a href=\"http://stars-facelift.dev.aashe.org/pages/report/stars-report-accuracy.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Data Accuracy webpage</a> for more information. </span></p>',1,'using-stars-data','',NULL,'2013-08-28 12:28:09'),
	(0,'Public Comment Period: Proposed Changes','2012-10-04 20:26:21',87,'<p>Welcome to the public comment period for STARS 2.0. This is the first major update of STARS since the release of the original <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/history/stars-10.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS 1.0 Technical Manual</a> in January 2010. &nbsp;The<em> STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</em>&nbsp;was created based on careful consideration of the feedback from you, the higher education community,&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/technical-advisors.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Advisors</a>, and the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/steering-committee.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Steering Committee</a>.&nbsp;We welcome and look forward to your comments, and want to thank you for being part of our engaged community.&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>An overview of the proposed changes to the <em>STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</em> is outlined below. &nbsp;Important documents and steps outlining how to submit feedback are included in \"<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-20-public-comment-period/public-comment-period-participation.html\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Period: Participation</a>.\" Answers to common inquiries may be found in \"<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-20-public-comment-period/public-comment-period-faqs.html\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Period: FAQs</a>.\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period will be open from Monday, October 8 through Friday,&nbsp;November 30, 2012. &nbsp;Feedback will not be considered outside of this timeframe. &nbsp;However, questions&nbsp;and comments about specific STARS credits or the overall program may always be emailed to&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.</p>\r\n<h2>Overview&nbsp;</h2>\r\n<p>The proposed changes for the draft of STARS 2.0 are considered Major Substantive&nbsp;Changes. &nbsp;Proposed changes for the draft of STARS 2.0 include:</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li>This proposed draft &nbsp;includes a single tier of 70 credits, reduced from 139 in STARS 1.2.</li>\r\n<li>New credits have been added, including credits covering student-run co-curricular programs, projects that utilize the campus as a living laboratory, air pollutant emissions, land use, biodiversity, wastewater treatment, workplace health and safety, and community stakeholder engagement.</li>\r\n<li>Former Tier Two credits have been consolidated into new credits and into existing credits as optional reporting fields.</li>\r\n<li>Credit titles have been simplified where possible.</li>\r\n<li>Minor edits have been made throughout to address inconsistencies (e.g. in reporting field language), provide additional guidance and clarification based on participant feedback, and correct typos and formatting issues.</li>\r\n<li>New standards and terms have been added throughout, as well as additional links to useful resources.</li>\r\n<li>New fields have been added to each subcategory and to the Innovation credits to allow institutions to upload images associated with STARS subcategories.</li>\r\n<li>The criteria for some credits have been altered significantly to reflect participant feedback, Technical Advisor discussions, and developments in the field (for example the Food and Beverage Purchasing, Affordability and Access, and Employee Compensation credits).</li>\r\n<li>Additional normalization factors have been added to some credits, for example the GHG Emissions, Energy Consumption, and Water Use. Credits are normalized by both weighted campus users and gross square feet of building space.</li>\r\n<li>The use of baselines in STARS has been changed significantly to give granting institutions greater flexibility in setting baselines for GHG emissions, energy consumption, waste generation and water use.</li>\r\n<li>Performance thresholds have been introduced into several credits to complement the use of baselines. Points are awarded for these credits based on a combination of reductions from baselines and performance in relation to minimum thresholds and performance targets.</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>For more information about the Technical Development process please see the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/technical_development_policy.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical&nbsp;Development Policy</a>&nbsp;(pdf) or visit the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/stars-policies.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Policies</a>&nbsp;page of the STARS website.</p>\r\n<p><strong id=\"internal-source-marker_0.47690877178683877\"> </strong></p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Visualization of Changes by Category</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This visual illustrates the proposed changes to the titles and arrangement of the sub-categories&nbsp;within each STARS Category.</p>\r\n<p><img src=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_2.0_visual_guide_by_category.png\" border=\"0\" width=\"902\" height=\"1004\" /></p>',1,'public-comment-period-proposed-changes','',NULL,'2012-10-22 15:04:07'),
	(1,'Public Comment Period: Participation','2012-10-04 20:43:56',88,'<p>Any individual is welcome to participate in the STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period. &nbsp;Individuals do not need to be affiliated with an AASHE member or <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/institutions/\" target=\"_self\">STARS Participant</a> institution to share feedback. Feedback may be submitted on behalf of an individual, an institution, an organization, or a business. All individuals and organizations submitting comments on specific credits or STARS subcategories must do so through the Public Comment Form which is linked below.</p>\r\n<p>AASHE recommends reading through the content of this web page, including the important documents below, prior to submitting comments.</p>\r\n<p>An overview of the proposed changes to the&nbsp;<em>STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</em>&nbsp;may be found in \"<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-20-public-comment-period/public-comment-period-proposed-changes.html\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Period: Proposed Changes</a>.\"&nbsp;Answers to common inquiries may be found in \"<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-20-public-comment-period/public-comment-period-faqs.html\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Period: FAQs</a>.\"&nbsp;</p>\r\n<h2>Step 1: Review Key Documents</h2>\r\n<p><strong>STARS 2.0 Vision Statement</strong><br /> <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/blog/opportunity-shape-vision-stars-20\" target=\"_self\"></a>The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/blog/opportunity-shape-vision-stars-20\" target=\"_self\">2.0 Vision Statement</a> was publicly posted in January 2012 and intended to respond to the many comments and suggestions that staff and STARS Steering Committee members have heard from the campus sustainability community prior to that time about STARS.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Technical Development Policy</strong><br /> <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/stars-policies.html\" target=\"_self\"></a>STARS seeks continuous improvement, while balancing the needs of our users. &nbsp;As a result, the STARS Steering Committee has adopted a <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/stars-policies.html\" target=\"_self\">Technical Development Policy</a> to guide how new information will be incorporated into STARS.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Summary of Proposed Changes</strong><br /> The <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_2.0_summary_of_proposed_changes_for_public_comment.pdf\" target=\"_self\">summary of proposed changes</a> (pdf) is a 6-page document that provides an &ldquo;at-a-glance&rdquo; overview of the major changes being proposed for STARS 2.0. &nbsp;The overview of major changes, edits to the introduction, and updates to the Innovation Category of the STARS Technical Manual are highlighted first. &nbsp;Then, the document breaks down the proposed changes to each STARS Category, sub-category, and credit where appropriate.</p>\r\n<p><strong>Proposed STARS 2.0 Technical Manual</strong><br /> Two versions of the <em>STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</em>&nbsp;are provided below. &nbsp;The first is a &ldquo;clean version&rdquo; which implements all the proposed changes.</p>\r\n<p>The &ldquo;tracked changes version&rdquo; of the draft of the <em>STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</em> includes tracked changes that reflect the exact edits made to the STARS 1.2 Technical Manual that resulted in the clean version of the draft.</p>\r\n<ul>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_2.0_technical_manual_draft_for_public_comment_clean_version.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS      2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</a> (Clean Version) (pdf)</li>\r\n<li><a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/stars_2.0_technical_manual_draft_for_public_comment_tracked_changes_version.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS      2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</a> (Tracked Changes Version) (pdf)</li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<p>Please note that the <em>STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment</em> is lengthy. &nbsp;Please plan accordingly so that all feedback is submitted through the public comment form between Monday, October 8 and Friday, November 30, 2012.&nbsp;All comments received will be carefully considered as part of the STARS 2.0 technical development process and shared publicly after the conclusion of the public comment period.</p>\r\n<h2>Step 2: Submit Feedback</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/a/aashe.org/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dGNwc2dKNlR5TkF5M2FtM01nWi1kN3c6MA#gid=0\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Form</a> is the vehicle to use to submit comments to AASHE concerning proposed changes at the credit and subcategory level in the <em>STARS 2.0 Technical Manual: Draft for Public Comment.</em></p>\r\n<h2 dir=\"ltr\">Step 3: Complete Survey</h2>\r\n<p dir=\"ltr\">AASHE asks that individuals participating in the STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period complete the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.surveygizmo.com/s3/972381/STARS-2-0-Public-Comment-Survey\" target=\"_self\">STARS 2.0 System-Wide Issues Survey</a>. This survey covers system-wide issues, including category weighting, scoring methodologies, and data verification in STARS. The survey consists of six multiple choice questions and should take no longer than 15 minutes to complete. The survey results will help inform the remainder of the STARS 2.0 development process.</p>',1,'public-comment-period-participation','',NULL,'2012-10-22 15:02:30'),
	(2,'Public Comment Period: FAQs','2012-10-04 20:58:48',89,'<p><a href=\"#process\" target=\"_self\">What was AASHE&rsquo;s process for making changes to the STARS Technical Manual between STARS 1.2 and STARS 2.0?</a><br /><a href=\"#participate\" target=\"_self\"> How do I participate?</a><br /><a href=\"#who_participate\" target=\"_self\"> Who can participate?</a><br /><a href=\"#how_long\" target=\"_self\"> How long is the public comment period?</a><br /><a href=\"#comments\" target=\"_self\"> What happens to my comments once they are submitted?</a><br /><a href=\"#next_steps\" target=\"_self\"> What are next steps after the public comment period?</a><br /><a href=\"#launch\" target=\"_self\"> When will STARS 2.0 be launched?</a><br /><a href=\"#reporting_tool\" target=\"_self\"> Will there be changes to the STARS Reporting Tool with the launch of STARS 2.0?</a><br /><a href=\"#contact\" target=\"_self\"> Who should I contact with questions?</a><br /><a href=\"#migrate\" target=\"_self\"> Will my STARS 1.2 data migrate into 2.0?</a></p>\r\n<p><strong><a name=\"process\" target=\"_self\"></a>What was AASHE&rsquo;s process for making changes to the STARS Technical Manual between STARS 1.2 and STARS 2.0?</strong><br />All feedback on ways to strengthen the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Manual</a>, and the overall STARS program, are taken into careful consideration by the AASHE staff. &nbsp;Credit-specific feedback is shared with the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/technical-advisors.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Advisors</a> for consideration when making enhancements to the STARS credits. &nbsp;Edits to the STARS credits are reviewed and subject to approval by the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/steering-committee.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Steering Committee</a>. &nbsp;<br />&nbsp;<br />For more information about the Technical Development process please see the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/technical_development_policy.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical&nbsp;Development Policy</a>&nbsp;(pdf) or visit the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/stars-policies.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Policies</a>&nbsp;page of the STARS website.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"participate\" target=\"_self\"></a>How do I participate?</strong><br />All individuals submitting comments must do so through the <a href=\"https://docs.google.com/a/aashe.org/spreadsheet/viewform?formkey=dGNwc2dKNlR5TkF5M2FtM01nWi1kN3c6MA#gid=0\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Form</a>. AASHE recommends reading through the content of the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-20-public-comment-period/public-comment-period-proposed-changes.html\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Period: Proposed Changes</a>&nbsp;and <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/get-involved/stars-20-public-comment-period/public-comment-period-participation.html\" target=\"_self\">Public Comment Period: Participation</a> webpages prior to participating in the public comment period.<br /><br />If you or your organization have more extensive comments (e.g. longer than 3,000 characters) or wish to submit a letter or other document, please email <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"who_participate\" target=\"_self\"></a>Who can participate?</strong><br />Any individual is welcome to participate in the STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period. &nbsp;Individuals do not need to be affiliated with an <a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/membership/member-directory\" target=\"_self\">AASHE member</a> or <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/institutions/\" target=\"_self\">STARS Participant institution</a> to share feedback. Feedback may be submitted on behalf of an individual, an institution, an organization, or a business.</p>\r\n<p>If you or your organization have more extensive comments (e.g. longer than 3,000 characters) or wish to submit a letter or other document, please email&nbsp;<a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"how_long\" target=\"_self\"></a>How long is the public comment period?</strong><br />The STARS 2.0 Public Comment Period will take place from Monday, October 8 through Friday, November 30, 2012. &nbsp;Feedback will not be considered outside of this timeframe. &nbsp;However, questions and comments about the specific STARS credit or overall program may always be emailed to <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"comments\" target=\"_self\"></a>What happens to my comments once they are submitted?</strong><br />All comments received will be carefully considered as part of the STARS 2.0 technical development process and shared publicly on the STARS website after the conclusion of the public comment period.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"next_steps\" target=\"_self\"></a>What are next steps after the public comment period?</strong><br />Once the public comment period closes, all comments, survey responses and&nbsp;other feedback received will be taken into consideration by AASHE staff. Recommendations for revisions will be sent to the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/steering-committee.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Steering Committee</a>. The STARS 2.0 Technical Manual will be finalized upon approval by the Steering Committee and a release date for STARS 2.0 will be announced.<br /><br />For more information about the Technical Development process please see the&nbsp;<a href=\"http://www.aashe.org/files/documents/STARS/technical_development_policy.pdf\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical&nbsp;Development Policy</a>&nbsp;(pdf) or visit the&nbsp;<a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/governance/stars-policies.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Policies</a>&nbsp;page of the STARS website.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"launch\" target=\"_self\"></a>When will STARS 2.0 be launched?</strong><br />AASHE anticipates that the STARS 2.0 Technical Manual will be available to the public sometime in 2013. However, no specific date has been designated at this time.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"reporting_tool\" target=\"_self\"></a>Will there be changes to the STARS Reporting Tool with the launch of STARS 2.0?</strong><br />Yes, in addition to an updated <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Manual</a>, AASHE will also be making enhancements to the STARS Reporting Tool. &nbsp;These enhancements are currently being finalized by the AASHE staff, but will be designed to increase the functionality and user experience when working in the STARS Reporting Tool.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"contact\" target=\"_self\"></a>Who should I contact with questions?</strong><br />All questions relating to STARS may be emailed to <a href=\"mailto:stars@aashe.org\" target=\"_self\">stars@aashe.org</a>.<br /><br /><strong><a name=\"migrate\" target=\"_self\"></a>Will my STARS 1.2 data migrate into 2.0?</strong><br />Institutions are responsible for reporting on the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/technical-manual.html\" target=\"_self\">STARS Technical Manual</a> that they register under. Therefore, if your institution registers when STARS 1.2 is the most up-to-date version of the STARS Technical Manual, it is under this version that it will to submit a STARS Report. However, if your institution has an active subscription to the STARS Reporting Tool when STARS 2.0 is launched, it will have the option to migrate its data to the most up-to-date version of STARS.<br /><br />Please see the <a href=\"https://stars.aashe.org/pages/about/faqs/reporting-and-information-sharing.html\" target=\"_self\">Reporting and Information Sharing FAQs</a>&nbsp;for details about migrating data.</p>',1,'public-comment-period-faqs','',NULL,'2012-10-08 12:00:50'),
